text:
pov salon // tirsdag d. 23. oktober kl. 13.00-14.30 inviterer @pov.international og @hovedbiblioteket_kbh til foredrag og debat med pov’s chefredaktør og usa-korrespondent, @annegrethefelter , om det kommende midtvejsvalg i usa.⠀ ”hvad nu usa?” er overskriften på oplægget, der spørger, hvad der egentlig foregår i washington d.c. og ude i landet.⠀
republikanerne står til at tabe repræsentanternes hus, og senatet er nu også i spil for første gang, fordi præsident donald trumps opinionsmålinger er så dårlige. ud over at det bliver spændende i sig selv at se, om republikanerne - og dermed trump - taber eller ej, så er der også udsigt til at få flest kvinder nogensinde valgt ind i kongressen. og det er et stort skifte - muligvis inspireret af #metoo-bevægelsen; der på en vis, bizar måde jo også kunne hænge sammen med trump og den heftige identitetspolitiske debat i det amerikanske.⠀
⠀
spørgsmålet er, hvad der sker, hvis demokraterne vinder huset (- og senatet?) tilbage?⠀
dels med den djævelsk dygtige reality-præsident trump? vil hans indre skabsdemokrat og forhandler titte frem, eller er han alligevel ligeglad med de folkevalgte og fortsætte linjen, hvor han kortslutter den politiske proces og kommunikerer direkte med de amerikanske vælgere på twitter?⠀
dels med kongressen. hvad vil den foretage sig? kan økonomien køre videre i det nuværende høje gear uanset, hvad man finder på i washington? bliver der rigsretssag, hvis demokraterne vinder kongressen? hvad med det regerende kaos i det hvide hus – har det overhovedet nogen indflydelse i en økonomi, der boomer.⠀ ⠀
der bliver god tid og plads til spørgsmål, debat og samtale, og alle er hjertelig velkomne.⠀
.⠀
.⠀
.⠀
#povsalon #usa #midtvejsvalg #donaldtrump #politik #københavnshovedbibliotek #povinternational #pointofviewinternational
name: POINT of VIEW International

text:
huge congratulations to 'milkman' by anna burns for winning the 50th man booker prize 📚🏆🎉 . . .  here's what chair of judges kwame anthony appiah had to say about this incredible novel: "none of us has ever read anything like this before. anna burns’ utterly distinctive voice challenges conventional thinking and form in surprising and immersive prose. it is a story of brutality, sexual encroachment and resistance threaded with mordant humour. set in a society divided against itself, 'milkman' explores the insidious forms oppression can take in everyday life.
⠀

i think this novel will help people think about #metoo ... it is to be commended for giving us a deep and subtle and morally and intellectually challenging picture of what #metoo is about". 📗
⠀

head in store to grab your copy - and check out the other fascinating reads that made the short list 🎉

#newleavesloves #annaburns #milkman #manbookerprize2018

⠀

i think this novel will help people think about #metoo ... it is to be commended for giving us a deep and subtle and morally and intellectually challenging picture of what #metoo is about". 📗
⠀

text:
⚠️⚠️long post may be triggering⚠️⚠️
•
•
•
•
•
•
•
•
i am so damn tired of feeling the way i do. i haven't really ever opened up to strangers about this, but i have a past of abuse that goes back to before i was three years old (mental, emotional and sexual). because of this i have an eating disorder, a ton of mental issues, trust issues,  commitment issues, and now it's all starting to effect my relationship. this relationship is something that i hold so close to my heart because it is so precious and i've worked so hard for it. i feel like i'm watching the most amazing thing that's ever happened to me slip through my fingers. i don't want it to happen and i'm not going to let it happen. i will fight this tooth and nail, and work my fingers to the bone for it.
i refuse to lay down and die.
i refuse to be a victim.
i refuse to let this take my freedom away.
i fucking refuse.
i want to be happy. 
i want to be healthy.
i want to be in love and not be afraid of what the future might bring to me.
i want to open this baggage, organize it, and demolish it.
abuse of any kind affects so many of us on here in so many different ways. for me it's caused anxiety, depression, unhealthy thought processes, a warped sense of who i am, and so many more things that i'm sure we all have gone through, or are going through.
i am ready to get better.
i am more than this. #metoo #iamnotavictim #takingbackmylife #strong

text: “perche’ proprio a me ?” e’ il primo pensiero che fai dopo la diagnosi di cancro. come un macigno ti schiaccia mente,corpo, anima e cuore, ti sprofonda negli abissi della disperazione. con rabbia, pensi :”anche questo mi doveva capitare” e ti senti la persona più sfortunata del mondo.  pian piano ti rialzi,inizi ad accettare e scopri che non sei sola e che molte donne condividono il tuo stesso dolore. il sorriso ritorna, la forza di combattere ti assale ed ecco che in quel  preciso momento  diventi “guerriera”! #fuckyoucancer #nonmollaremai #breastcancerwarrior #breastcancer #breastcancerawareness #cancroalseno #cancer #cancersurvivor #vincoio #metoo #leguerrieresciencesartsandevents

text:
what a beautiful thing you've done for you and your children, ella 💙 ✨ @rebelthriver 💙⚓
_
@regran_ed from @rebelthriver -  in solidarity with all the others who have suffered or died at the hands of an abuser i recognize october as domestic violence awareness month.

did you know that in the usa, 3 women die every single day, and a woman is beaten every 12 seconds due to domestic violence. also, the a high percentage of children who live with domestic violence in their homes, grow up to do the same. the cycle of violence runs deep.
my ex-husband had been terribly abused as a child. 
i broke the cycle for my children. it was the hardest thing that i ever had to do. being a survivor has altered every molecule and minute of my life. today helping others recover from abuse is what i am called to do. rebel thriver welcomes all of the survivors out there to join us. you can learn to find your voice if you haven't already. there is a way through the pain that you may be in. here you can get advice, be educated, supported, and loved. knowing that someone else understands the kinda crazy that you live with in your head is priceless. it is possible to live a thriving life. you just have to believe. 
xo ella

text:
to all the people who talk shit behind my back, like “why is she always so naked? এত গা দেখানোর কি হইল?”..
because i like being naked. because i can spare myself from being over conscious about my scars, flaws, and imperfections of all sorts. because it’s very liberating. because i can feel the air better. because clothes don’t save you from sexual assault, and i know that very well. and i’m a way better person than most of you will ever be. not because i show more skin than most of you do, but because i don’t judge people. i don’t belittle people based on their gender, sexual orientation, age, colour, social status. i don’t place people’s ‘shame’ on their physical exterior. i don’t hate people for who they are, what they wear or don’t wear, whether they are covered or naked. and i don’t build relationships of any kind based on how much money a person has. so feel free to kiss my ass while i poop in your mouths. happy thursday 🤘🏽

•

text:
happy navami to all of you. may good win over all evils. the world at times, feels evil and vile, what with all the #metoo coming out of the wood. people you looked up is crumbling like cookies.  we are all vulnerable, we have all suffered, faced this and blamed ourselves. 
and then, you meet some people who are so full of goodness and sincerity that they restore faith and hope. jaya bajaj @nsk.jaya  is one such person. i have met her a few times and each time come back  enveloped in her warmth. she makes these amazing pickles under the brand @aamrabynsk employing only women and using age-old recipes and lovingly prepares these jars of pickle, as if to give away to family instead for commercial purpose.  each jar carries a bit of her warmth, me thinks! that's why her pickles, chutneys are soo good❤ trust me the pickles are so unlike the commercial ones, they are aged upto three years, before they land up on your table!!! i should know, for i have spent time in her factory, though that 'factory' word does not suit her space.  she has these fabulous gift boxes for gifting (i hate to part  with them)!!! go get some and gift yourself this festive season. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#pickles #indianfood #delicious #vegeterian #madewithlove#foodonmytable #gifts #traditional #familyrecipes #love #foodblogger #instafoodie

text: השבוע בטיים אאוט: שנה למהפכת #metoo – פרויקט מיוחד מנסה לבדוק לאן ממשיכים מכאן עם הנשים הבולטות של המהפכה, איפה נכנס הג'יהאד הפמיניסטי? ומה הסיפור של זן הגברים החדשים שצמחו פה על הדרך? כל הטעויות האפשריות שנעשו בתרבות הפופולרית בדרך להעצמה נשית ולמה עדיין בקולנוע סצינות של תקיפה מינית מוצגות כדבר מחרמן? בבחירות: סקירת הקמפיינים מעוררת געגועים לנרקיסיזם של פעם וטיפים מניצן הורוביץ, האיש שהיה הכי קרוב להחליף את חולדאי. בבריאות: כל מה שצריך לדעת על בהלת החצבת המתפשטת בעיר והשיטה החדשה שתחליף את נוגדי הדיכאון שכולנו משתמשים בהם. באוכל: כל מנות האבוקדו הכי שוות בעיר והמקום החדש והמדובר ששם אותו במרכז, באלכוהול: איך הפך הג'ין טוניק מדרינק של דודות לדבר הכי לוהט בסצינת האלכוהול? החיים קצרים, קחו טיים אאוט. להשיג בבית הקפה השכונתי האהוב עליכם ובסניפי אמ:פמ.

text:
a dramatic representation of what happens in the streets of mumbai every morning. just saying!!! 🤷🏼‍♀️
.
i am not here to criticise any government or overlook the efforts being made in this direction. i am just putting my point forward for it is equally disturbing and uncomfortable for both the onlooker and the slum dweller to engage in such an activity in the open. .
while the “mahanagri” was declared open defecation free in early 2018, the statistics reveal that nearly 50 lakh residents of the city’s notified slums are served by 750-odd community toilet blocks constructed under the world bank-initiated slum sanitation programme (ssp). these toilets have 26,379 seats, which approximately means one toilet seat to be shared by 190 users, as against the mcgm-accepted who norms of one toilet per 50 people. .
the first solution that comes to my mind is to stop making the construction of toilets an election agenda as it is used by the politicians to reap short term benefits. once the elections are won, the plight of the common slum dweller goes down the drain. we can even go ahead to build a ppp model for construction and operation of public sanitation housing which might work for the benefit of all.
.
just a thought in interest of all. if you think this helps, please share and let’s help create some awareness.
.
p. s. - the statistics have been used from an article published in june 2018.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
working in a particular sector of agriculture (supply of produce), sexual harassment has been a huge factor in where i am today in my career. how has this affected me as a #woman in #supply of our farmers’ produce: • i have #changed jobs until i found a company that has a zero tolerance for #sexual harassment • i have been told in the past to “show more skin to get more sales” #boobs • i’ve been told at @brisbanemarketplace that i look tired and #unattractive by the time i’ve walked around the markets looking at produce • a former employee told me not to wear my safety boots as they were “ugly” on me even though #forklifts zoomed around me continuously while completing my work #doessafetycomefirst • my clothes have been commented on endlessly at work, what colors suit me, and what don’t? #wtf • i’ve had forklift drivers stop me every few meters to invite me out on dates with them, despite my shiny bling on my finger i was so blessed to get from my fiancée #hewontknow apparently • the same forklift drivers have patted their laps and asked me to “ride with them” - which a previous supervisor found funny at the time • i have felt #stupid, #incompetent and not good enough. • i’ve been called a #cocktease for simply being me, i’m sure having a passion for fruit and vegetables warrants this? 🙄 • i’ve been pressured into very #awkward work situations where i didn’t feel i had a voice, don’t forget - it’s intimidating working in a male dominated industry • i’ve sought advice from friends who are farmers, my uncles, my fiancée, all the good men i know, asking where am i going wrong to attract this unwarranted attention #selfdoubt • i’ve been sexually harassed so many times at work that i became #depressed because i felt it was all my #fault for not saying f*ck off to them • i have hated myself, truly truly hated myself because of it. i dressed myself down entirely, stopped wearing make up, my work was affected, i never once wore anything but long pants because i was scared i would be #commented on relentlessly. 
all i want to do is #support farmers, but gee, it can take a toll. 
help stop sexual harassment!! 93% is not good enough for aus women!!
#metoo

text:
hi friends,
how about a circle of conversations on #metooindia , about our stories, and how we can create a safe space to open up our hearts? 
the me too movement, with many local and international alternatives, is a movement against sexual harassment and sexual assault. #metoo spread virally in october 2017 as a hashtag used on social media in an attempt to demonstrate the widespread prevalence of sexual assault and harassment, especially in the workplace. it picked up in india 26th september onwards when tanushree dutta was asked about the metoo movement and she shared story.

rashmi sinha in collaboration with the gender lab invite you to join the circle this sunday, 21st october 2018💫
time: 4:30 pm to 6:30 pm
confirm your presence by sending a text to:  9830704898
place:
brm home
1st floor, pitruchhaya bungalow, 
damodar mhatre road, mhatre wadi, 
dahisar west (near nagrik stores)

text: it’s #lgbthistorymonth so i’m holding space for the black queer people who this country has historically failed to protect, like the new jersey 7. 🥀 in 2006, they went to jail for “gang assault” after defending themselves against a man who threatened to r*pe them “straight” & assaulted them. their story raises a few questions: are black queer people not allowed to protect ourselves? and if our justice system doesn’t serve everyone, how can we call it just? you can read the full story for @blackyouthproject at the link in my bio. • i’m also part of a panel on redefining self care at @envsnfest this saturday! i’ll be talking about sex/sexuality, as per usual. hope to see some of you there.💖

text:
to all those strong ladies who fought against / fighting against depression due to sexual abuse, bullying,body shaming, domestic abuse
i can hear you my sister
i can hear those silent whispers
behind your strong cold face
i can sense the unknown pain burried deep within you.
there is nothing in this world can pay for that shattered innocence of yours..
but sister let's join our hands together now
we don't want our saplings and sisters to suffer the same pain of ours
we know how hard it is to happen  to anyone
after years of education,we found the root cause of our pain
let's put an end to those lusty eyes which sees us as sex objects
it's time to show our strong face
let's war against predators
come out sister
make them run away
for a safe environment of our sisterhood 💜✨
it's time for our  kaali face 🙂 
with love,
one of your warrior sister 💓☮️ #metoo

text: khali is a goddess who feels the sensuality and perfection of her feminine form. she is perfectly comfortable in her skin. and in that perfection she can tame any poisonous snake (symbolism for sure!) she dresses in a silk ribboned skirt upon which she knots the skulls of anyone who dares to impede her personal journey through life. and so she steps in the dance of life with the rattle of empty voices trailing behind. #khali #shaunacrandallart #watercolorportrait  #goddess #womenpower #metoo #watercolorart #watercolorpainting #watercoloring #crecsentmoon #fullmoon #moon #wicca #wiccan #beautifulstranger #snaketamer #dancer #greysky #womenrule #queen

text:
this is my daughter. today my daughter contacted me over derogative comments being made on her social media account by an individual. as vial as the comments were, my first response was to tell her to ignore and block the person. which she said she had and even made her page now private, but it appears they had made other accounts and previoulsy followed her, so the comments continued. she contacted her dad, he  suggested she deactivate her account for now. but is this the overall answer? 
perhaps the most important element to addressing online harassment is behaving like it is happening in the “real world” abuse is abuse. online spaces are created shaped and used by real humans, with real bodies and real feelings. 
harassment in online spaces is just as real and harmful as when it happens on the street, in schools and in workplaces. 
eradicating online harassment won’t be easy, but it’s time that we put even more pressure on social networks to implement policies, efficient tools, and algorithms against online harassers. there is a difference between freedom of speech and hate speech. threats, bullying and harassment are unacceptable, and we shouldn’t let ourselves become desensitized to them, or even normalise it as i believe we are.

so long to perfection, body shaming, impossible beauty standards, the haters, the trolls, “thin-spiration,” fat shaming, vial name calling, mental health judgments. shout out to all of you fighting to love yourself in a world constantly telling you that you’re not enough,you are enough, you are so enough, it’s absolutely insane how enough you are.
you are worthy, you are beautiful, you are wonderfully made. there is no mistakes on you, rest in that. love yourself, don’t be ashamed of that x 💛

at only age 5, i learned the life i knew was not that innocent and naive! i learned its up to me to make my own destiny and there on out started fighting my own battles. today someone asked me why i feel proud to be myself? i am proud because i stood up for what i always believed in! when i turned 10 i was called ugly, patni,too dark, not as fair like my mother. bangali's saying why didnt i look as good as mother who was lighter. why does it even matter what the color of my skin is, or what i wear? i cannot take none of that in heaven with me. i can only take my heart with me. today while i volunteered at the cancer art center and i gave my speach it reminded me of all the pain i overcame in life and how beautiful of a woman that made me today. i love yall! dont let no one bring you down. #gorgeoussisters

text:
word of the day is consent.

first of all i've been up since 3am... i truly believe the best ideas come in the midst of the night.  this post is created at 5am.  first of all let's cut the bs.. consent is not just sexual... it's emotional, it's spiritual, physical, and intellectual. ask yourself do i consent? in whatever the situation may be. its okay to say no. 
i am going to talk about consent so unapologetically. so you better listen. 
lack of consent is rape.

if you haven't been consentual, you are constantly abusing my right to consent. 
so you imagine a person hasn't given you consent on anything that is valuable to them, do you then feel you have the right to take it, or do you consider that person's voice and ask them for it.

we live in a society where everything is so available that forget to ask the most basic questions.

don't be dragged in situations where you feel uncomfortable.

don't underestimate the power of consent.

don't let your ego get the best of you, when you hear the word no.

#itsnotthatdeep but it is tho... i have the right to consent.

consent is not just on... heterosexual relationships
same sex couples
children
vulnerable adults
it's on.... friends
family
situationships
workplaces
public spaces.. consent is part of  our everyday landuage.

i don't consent in you looking at me,  in a way that makes me uncomfortable.

i don't consent in small talks.

don't assume me, you better ask me.

ask and you shall not receive.. it's okay to say no

watch out for people's intentions. 
#consent #youhavetherighttoremainsilent #unapologetic #staywoke #spiritually #emotionally #freedom #idontconsent #metoo #inmyfeelings

i consent in you respecting me. ps saida vedasto.

text:
people are waking up and as they do many are screaming for justice!! it’s time. time for a new way of thinking and a new way of leading which in turn needs a new paradigm of what justice actually is and how it can serve us as a people, not the other way around. 
the old way, the old paradigm of justice for many was based on hammurabi’s code dating back to ancient mesopotamia known as lex talionis, or the law of retribution. in lay mans speak we say “an eye for an eye”. if something happens to me i have the right to do the same in return. yet any parent watching their children play when someone gets hurt knows an eye for an eye only causes more pain. so why do we continue to believe this idea and let it play out in our society? 
to see how an eye for an eye doesn’t work in the legal system we need simply to see a father interviewed on the steps of the court house after the person who has killed his daughter was sentenced. upon being asked how he feels, he replies “justice may have been served, but it will never bring back my daughter”. the man feels hollow, grief struck, a feeling that no amount of inflicting pain on another can heal. grief is about loss and requires a person to move completely through the cycle to come to a new place, or paradigm, of how they will live life. that has nothing to do with inflicting pain on another, which comes from anger. an emotion in this situation that is working to protect the feeler so they can go inside and grieve. 
an eye of an eye is two negatives trying to make a positive, and everyone knows that doesn’t work. 
i suggest we need a new way of thinking about justice and the answer lies in the symbol of justice itself – the scales. the scales symbolize, amongst other things, balance. balance of the two sides brings harmony. harmony doesn’t come from revenge. it can only come from healing. 
justice is about rebalance, not retribution. 
the dali lama has been talking of forgiveness and compassion on the world stage as an envoy for the tibetan people who have suffered incredibly under foreign rule. nature calls for balance. wrongs must be bought back into balance. it’s how we go about this rebalancing process that wil

text:
it is said, that when evil reigned unabated,
arrogance defeated man,
when even the god's were powerless,
laid low by ignorance...
it is then that she rose,
oh mother divine! 
pure and serene,
with righteous and purpose, 
purging the world of evil, 
felling the demon of arrogance, 
putting an end to injustice, 
and resetting the balance, 
that had been tilted. 
#metoo #dushera #woman #womenempowerment #womenpower

summary- keshav is a teacher in iit tution classes in delhi. he is having a tough time in his life because of the breakup with his ex-girlfriend zara. keshav tries everything to win the love of his life back but zara doesnt wish to give another chance. zara on the other hand is engaged to raghu, a business tycoon. but the pace of the story changes when zara is found dead in her college hostel room 105. who took zara’s life is the question no one seem to have an answer for! keshav being deeply in love with her starts on a journey to seek the answers. will keshav be able to reveal who the killer was? .
🍁
.
review- chetan bhagat has definitely returned with a bang. this is his 1st shot at thrillers & its a good one. what i loved is the plot of the story, from college love to kashmir terrorism everything has been included. the book serves an unending suspense ride for everyone. if you are a bhagat fan & are looking for a light & fun read this is the book you can order right away.
.
🍁
.
rating- 3.5/5 ⭐️
.

text:
‪⚠️trigger warning: ‬
sexual violence⚠️
this is a call for collaboration on an art piece i’m working on to represent survivors/victims of sexual assault. this is an opportunity to have your story heard, 100% anonymously. my “survivor” series will focus on two things: ‪1. celebrating the resilience of those who have experienced/witnessed rape, harassment or assault and 2. visually demonstrating the magnitude of this issue. i’m painting on a very large rectangular piece and i want to fill the canvas with quotes from survivors/victims.‬
•
‪the quotes taken from survivors’ stories will be printed in tiny letters so that the overwhelming amount of text represents that this is an overwhelming problem. across the canvas in big letters will be “our stories matter” (or similar verbiage. this is still a work in progress.)‬
•
‪this is an opportunity to make your voice heard with 100% anonymity and zero judgment. i will be your confessional, this is your time to speak out and have your story shared. you can pm me your quotes or stories and they can be as vague or detailed as you like.‬
•
‪i am a survivor of multiple assaults and i want to use my art as my voice and represent your voices as well. for your safety/privacy, no names or identifying factors will be used in this piece. use this opportunity to be courageous and speak out. your story matters.‬
•
‪you are not alone and we are stronger together. you can pm me if you’re comfortable doing so. if you’d like to share this post, please do. if you want to tag a survivor you know, i suggest you share the post privately to ensure safety and confidentiality.‬
•
‪i want as many people as possible to have the opportunity to participate in this project. everyone should have the chance to be heard. big hugs to all who have gone through unspeakable traumas and yet wake up every day and survive. i know how difficult this topic is to discuss, but it is important that we make our voices known. ‬
‪•‬
‪thank you for reading, sharing and having the bravery to participate in this project. 🖤#timesup #metoo #survivor #speakout #ibelieveyou #nomeansno #consent #whyididntreport #calltoaction #art #collaboration #strongertogether

text:
i’ve been thinking about this a lot lately. detoxing brings out a lot of demons, memories, and horrible emotions. 
i’m still having horrible nightmares. i’m still having withdrawals. i’m still wanting drugs. 
i’m still battling this everyday and i know i will continue to battle this. some days are easier than other. i love the few mornings i wake up with a headache. 
i’ve really been trying to think about how this all started, why it started, why my mind thought it needed this. how in the hell at twelve years old i figured out that pills would help me hide from the memories i was trying so hard to forget. 
a few friends have told me to start opening up about the things that happened. 
so here it goes,
when i was seven years old, my aunt would watch me sometimes. i loved her so much, she always showed me so much attention and love, which coming from a family of four children and constantly being abused by my dad, attention from her was perfect. 
one sunday, i was at her house. we were making cookies and i was sitting on the counter eating cookie dough. she started to act differently, it made me uncomfortable but as a seven year old i didn’t even know what it was about. next thing i know she is touching me and forcing my shorts down. she then decided to penetrate me with a kitchen knife. at that point i mentally disappeared, removing myself from the situation. after that, all i remember was being at the hospital with my parents. i remember taking a long time to heal and i stayed home from school for over a month. as i grew up, i learned that my aunt had basically given me an at home hysterectomy. 
she took away a lot from me that day, my childhood, my trust, my ability to have children one day.
i guess with the drugs it was easier to hide from this. i didn’t know how to deal with it. i still don’t. 
i’m just slowly trying to figure out what it is that’s destroying me and how to “fix” myself. 
some days i’m happy to be alive. but most days, i wonder if it’s really worth it. #abuse #abusesurvivor #metoo

text:
“we must not forget that for every story told by women, there are dozens of stories untold”- article by shri.ram madhav on #metoo movement.

after #metoo, a better india
the movement has highlighted the need for workplaces to be free of harassment and intimidation. moving forward, society must make women’s equality an article of faith
written by ram madhav |
updated: october 18, 2018 12:10:03 am
next

workplace harassment is not just a frivolous crime — it is a violent crime. 
#metoo has become a strong movement in india. it is courageous on the part of those large number of women who are coming out in the open with their stories of workplace harassment and unwanted sexual overtures from male colleagues. in a predominantly conservative setting like that of our society, these acts are no mean feats. if not for any other reason, these women need the support of society at large because they have mustered the courage to speak up.

workplace harassment is not just a frivolous crime — it is a violent crime. violence need not always be physical. it can be mental. it can be emotional. through words and deeds, a person has the potential to outrage the feelings and emotions of another. this is much easier and more hurtful in the context of sexual harassment and intimidation.

in fact, this is the elephant in the workplace almost everywhere in india. we didn’t speak about it much, didn’t do enough to arrest it, didn’t try to act against the perpetrators in a big way. social mores, stigma and familial sensibilities have thus far led the victims to silently suffer violations without raising their voices too much. but that doesn’t mean it is a small or a non-issue. at last, now when women have started speaking up, we realise that it is not just a minor issue, but a monster.

we must not forget that for every story told by women, there are dozens of stories untold. maybe those stories that find space in the media belong mostly to visible professions like the media and film industry, but the victims are everywhere, from villages to rich urban households. it is the fear of societal reaction and stigma that forces them to suffer silently or in extreme cases, to end their lives.

we must not forget that for every story told by women, there are dozens of stories untold. maybe those stories that find space in the media belong mostly to visible professions like the media and film industry, but the victims are everywhere, from villages to rich urban households. it is the fear of societal reaction and stigma that forces them to suffer silently or in extreme cases, to end their lives.

text:
most cases of sexual abuse are never reported. i didn’t report either of mine. ⠀
⠀
i was molested by a kid in my class when i was 7 years old. it literally happened in my classroom. this was the last day i wore a skirt or dress to school for a long time. ⠀
⠀
the boy i sat next to in the back of the classroom took it upon himself to explore my body underneath my skirt and underwear. ⠀
⠀
i froze. i was terrified. i had no idea what was happening, but i knew it was wrong and shouldn’t be happening. i was confused. i didn’t want to get him in trouble. ⠀
⠀
i could have screamed. i mean, my teacher and classmates were right. there. if i could have done that day over again, i would’ve screamed and punched him in the cajones. ⠀
⠀
but what i really want to know is: “what was happening to that little boy at home?? where did that cycle begin???”⠀
⠀
what i do know is: i•▲m committed to ending this cycle, and my part in doing that is being vulnerable and open about my own experiences so i can empower others to also speak up.⠀
⠀
when i was raped, i felt like it was my fault somehow. i was asleep and woke up to a stranger invading my body.⠀
⠀
the shame and embarrassment was so overwhelming that i only told 2 girlfriends. ⠀
⠀
i didn’t know who else to tell or how to even handle that situation. it was like i had no voice...⠀
⠀
i didn’t realize at the time that this fear was a product of the conditioning and programming from our own society. ⠀
⠀
when children speak up about their sexual abuse from people they trust, they’re often told to be quiet about it. even worse, they are sometimes told that no one believes them. ⠀
⠀
when women speak up about their boss sexually abusing them, their careers, character, and livelihood are threatened - so other women choose to be quiet when it happens to them. ⠀
⠀
when i found my power in sharing my experiences, i made a promise that i will never not be a voice about this issue that’s been going on for thousands of years!⠀
⠀
speak up. your voice is worthy of being heard. #whyididntreport @whyididntreportit⠀
⠀
#metoo #youareworthy #useyourvoice #iloveyou #riseup #timesup

text:
mia farrow habla sobre la conducta sexual inapropiada en hollywood: "sé lo que es ser interrogada en las audiciones". el pasado lunes por la noche en beverly hills, la legendaria actriz de 73 años, mía farrow, recordó su tiempo en hollywood: "yo sé lo que es estar a tientas y humillada en las audiciones". "un año disculpándome con el jefe del estudio que acaba de meterme la lengua en la garganta". esto sucedió en ocasión de recibir de manos de su hijo ronan farrow, ganador del premio pulitzer, el premio elle's legend, uno de los ocho premios que se entregaron durante un programa de tres horas organizado por mindy kaling, por el 25 aniversario de la revista elle women in hollywood. "la verdad es que mi madre siempre se ha sentido incómoda con la fama y los elogios", dijo ronan al entregarle a su madre el premio. la audiencia estuvo compuesta por homenajeados que incluyeron a lady gaga, charlize theron, sarah paulson, shonda rhimes, keira knightley, yara shahidi y angela bassett, entre otros.  #soyjuanpa
---------------------------------------- #miafarrow #metoo #abusossexuales #hollywood @ladygaga #charlizetheron #keiraknightley #angelabasset #juanpallywood #juanpa

text:
when i was in london last month, i didn't just go to harrods.  i also went to harvey nichols.  on the pavement around the store, pink quotes were painted to celebrate the #yearofthewoman. ♀️ harvey nichols rebranded themselves for the month as holly nichols for their, "let's hear it for the girls" campaign.  for more details:  https://is.gd/bzml1r

there were some truly great quotes from some seriously iconic women.  below are the longer ones in the third collage since they're a bit harder to see.
.
"oh, you have the tail twisted.  i am not what you thought.  you had me down as a damsel?  darling, i'm the wolf." ~srw.
.
"i raise up my voice, not so i can shout, but so that those without a voice can be heard." ~malala yousafzai.
.
"there is no limit to what we, as women, can accomplish." ~michelle obama.
.
"each time a woman stands up for herself, without knowing it, possibly, without claiming it, she stands up for all women." ~maya angelou.
.
"to tell a woman everything she cannot do, is to tell her what she can do." ~unknown.
.
"it took me quite a long time to develop a voice.  and now that i have it, i am not going to be silent." ~madeleine albright

text:
lessons in #resilience— 
the other night i woke up in a panic, crying. i couldn’t understand why i was feeling so uneasy, why my dreams turned suddenly violent and grotesque, why i was struck with a dreadful feeling i wasn’t safe. those feelings dissolved the next morning as the day resumed its easy rhythm, and later i realized why. 
i used to work so hard not to commit the date of my sexual assault to memory, yet each year the anniversary of the event would unnerve me. 
for weeks this time of year would be steeped in anxiety and i’d find myself operating in (or sometimes hijacked by) fight-flight-freeze. 
but with a smile in my heart i can tell you it wasn’t like that this year. though the nightmare was jarring and i certainly had a few tender days, none of it lingered. instead, i’ve been able to create space to connect with others, with myself, with nature, with the world. more space for more of this 👆🏼.
you might think the fallen tree in this photo has seen better days, that it’s broken and headed for decay. you might assess its fall from higher up the bank where the tree originally stood tall, observe the branches ripped off the side of its neighbor as it crashed into the creek, see the splintered wood and think, “what a pity.” but follow the length of it across the water and you’d see from the thickness of its trunk, snaking up the slope and out of sight, that this remarkable tree found a way to thrive. 
what i am trying to say is: i am so grateful for this journey. i am so grateful for my healing and for the ways i‘ve seen myself grow. #posttraumaticgrowth 
#metoo #healingjourney #ptsd #believesurvivors

text:
idontwannabeyouanymore
•
•
behind the scenes: i was so excited to shoot this set of pictures! i knew exactly how i wanted these to look and i was so stoked to use them for my new blog design (check it out in the link in my bio 😉)! i fell in love with this top from @jamescboutique in the summer because it was classy and fun, you can dress it up or down, and it can totally adjusted to fit you perfectly!! #matchmadeinheaven so we get downtown to shoot this look on a busy saturday morning, just steps away from one of my favorite farmers markets in lexington. after a few compliments, i feel really empowered. women telling me “wow that top looks amazing on you!” and “i so wish i could rock that!” i tell them “you can, you so can!” you can rock anything as long as you love it. and then comes an older couple, the woman is giving me a sheepish smile and a look that says “you go girl.” before she has time to really say anything, her male counterpart whistles. at me. while still holding her hand. a middle aged man, walking down the street with another woman, cat called a 21 year old girl. my whole mood changed. i no longer felt empowered by the blouse i was wearing, i felt dehumanized. i stood there stunned for moment, hearing the question “are you serious?” slip from my mouth. i turned to my dear friend, the hairs on my necks standing straight up, and asked if she’d gotten all the shots we needed. i was done, i wanted out. out of the situation, out of the shirt, out of the spotlight. not a single word was spoken to me by this man and yet i wanted to be as far from him as possible. my favorite shirt, stained with what i hope is the worst memory i have of another human and a set of pictures to remind me of it. i am a woman. that’s why it matters. #inherhumbleopinionblog #conquerfromwithin #blogged

take the vow.

text:
some days are harder than others and i think that it's only normal to not always feel 100%. today has been one of those days.

i don't know about you ladies but sometimes i find myself having to stop and remind myself of what my big picture is. what it is i want to accomplish and what i still need to do to get there. 
i know that on my instagram story i have asked you ladies to feel free and ask me questions to get to know me a little better, but here's a little something about me. 
i, in a million years would have not pictured myself doing martial arts and teaching self-defense classes. i was never the athletic type and to this day i still will tell you, that i'm not athletic at all 🙈

but i do have a vision and calling that i think is much larger than myself. i don't want to leave this world without making a positive impact on this planet and i know it sounds very cliche but i honestly wish nothing more but to help others. 
i started empowered self-defense to try and empower over women to be more than they think themselves to be. to feel safe. free to go travel and explore the world and not be afraid. to live life at its fullest. 
i know i still have a lot of work to do and i know my ultimate goal of opening up my own school is still a little further down the line. believe me when i say that i truly enjoy what i do. my life journey has not been easy, but to see and hear any positive feedback from you ladies does mean so much to me. it helps me focus on why it is i'm doing this. 
i really do hope i get to see all of you in class one day and please don't be shy, feel free to have conversations with me. i promise i don't bite and i'd love nothing more than to help you out in anyway that i can.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

#empoweredselfdefense #selfdefense #girlpower #survive #survivor #womenempoweringwomen #selfdefenseawareness  #selfcare #loveyourself #fightlikeagirl #wednesday #metoo #hitlikeagirl #downey #calstatela #eastlosangeles #eastla #humpday #bellgardens #october #domesticviolenceawareness #motivation #wecandoit

but i do have a vision and calling that i think is much larger than myself. i do not want to leave this world without making a positive impact on this planet and i know it sounds very cliche but i honestly wish nothing more but to help others. 
i staed empowered self-defense to try and empower over women to be more than they think themselves to be. to feel safe. free to go travel and explore the world and not be afraid. to live life at its fullest. 
i know i still have a lot of work to do and i know my ultimate goal of opening up my own school is still a little fuher down the line. believe me when i say that i truly enjoy what i do. my life journey has not been easy, but to see and hear any positive feedback from you ladies does mean so much to me. it helps me focus on why it is i am doing this. 
i really do hope i get to see all of you in class one day and please do not be shy, feel free to have conversations with me. i promise i do not bite and i'd love nothing more than to help you out in anyway that i can.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

date night with the husband after a long time and i pulled out this wispy striped beautifully textured maheshwari, the color of kesar mango, with an antique gold tissue border and pallu from @rehwasociety that's a richly delicious saree. i blinged it up (see stories) for a wedding the last time i wore it but dressed it down for dinner sunday night, pairing it with a fun and flirty natural dyed ajrakh tunic with gathers from @paromitabanerjee that made me get all girly and twirly. the beautiful blue green wooden necklace is from my summer loot from @varnamcraftcollective and the silver with work in the same color palette from #karmasuthrajewelry. autumn has finally arrived in our part of the world, so bundle up i did before we walked out.
.
sunday morning was spent pouring over articles, twitter feeds and instagram stories about the #metoo movement gaining traction in india with a wave of allegations against prominent men in media and advertising in recent days. i had missed it all until a post from a friend prompted the hours long reading up. all it took was for one or two women to overcome their fear and get the courage to speak out, and the flood gates opened. i salute them! it was heartening to see how women have been supporting other women without judgment and offering help, support and even employment to those who are risking their careers by taking a stand. i was also glad to see a couple of companies take swift action and place these men on leave while they investigated the allegations. corporate india needs to send a message that this will not be tolerated in the workplace or outside, and maybe then the government and other sectors will follow, though i don't have much hope for that in the near term. and then i read geetanjali arora's post and comments and realized we still have a long way to go in educating people about how power dynamics, toxic culture and the vicious cycle of sexual harassment works. 🤦‍♀️ still, we have to start somewhere.
.
.
#iwearhandloom #iwearhandloomsarees #sareelove #sareesofinstagram #weavesofindia #maheswari #ajrakh #naturaldye #

text:
this week we begin posting we shall be heard stories submitted by you! to share your story, send us a private message. thank you for your bravery in telling your story lisa marie! “my #weshallbeheard story... the past few weeks have been very hard for me. listening to the testimony, i went through many emotions as has been the case over the past few years. i was sexually assaulted in a medical facility on thanksgiving day. it will be 4 years this coming thanksgiving. he took so much from me including thanksgiving day itself, as i have not celebrated since. it is always so hard for woman to have the courage to come forward with their story, just to be shot down and questioned. i chose to report it right away and even though it's been years, he has never lost his job. the message that that sends to me is it's okay for even a medical professional to do this. every detail of my life has been questioned. i have nothing in my past that i am at all ashamed of.  i haven’t done anything to deserve his criminal act against me and then to be violated again by the questions they ask. what i have done or not done in my life is my business. this was never okay with me, and i was unconscious. even the detective seemed annoyed when he got the call and had to come to the police department early on thanksgiving morning to take my statement. he felt the need to tell me at least three times! it felt like he wanted me to know i shouldn’t have interrupted his day with family while no one cared about mine. my fight continues..”
.
.
.
#whywemarch #womenempowerment #womensmarch #womensmarchonphiladelphia #phillywomenrally #wmop2019 #metoo #timesup #activisim
name: Women’s March On Philadelphia

text: more and more people talk about #believewomen and #notyourfault when it comes to the trauma. but it’s time we remind everyone that it’s not your fault for how your mind and body react post trauma. you did not choose or cause yourself to have #ptsd the intensity of it is not your fault. you did not choose to not have ptsd and just because you don’t does not mean you were not assaulted. everyone reacts differently in the situation and after the situation. if you struggle with sucial thoughts post assault it is not your fault. please reach out. i promise it will feel better eventually. get help now before it’s too late. #dontactonit 1 (800)-273-8255  it is not your fault.  #metoo  1 (800)-656-4673  my dm’s are always open. #ibelieveyou

text:
ladies! join two of today's leading female shamans, rebecca haywood & tatyana rae von knobelsdorff, and unfold into the shameless feminine…
.
“we each have felt it. her yearning to release, to break open, to drink of her sorrow and sing of her rage. and we must. it is our unfolding— petals once held in shadow turning to the sun." ~rh .
.
rebecca & tatyana invite you into a sacred circle of women and into the unfolding... they will guide you into a shamanic dreaming process through which you will unfold into the organic wisdom of your feelings and allow them to move through you, to move you... closer, deeper, dissolved into their delicious invitation.
.
”we are designed to be obsessed with the calling heard within our hearts— constantly seeking to reunite with breath, as life, as divinity." ~tvk
.
where is the shameless feminine calling you?
.
@aumandgarden sunday, october 28th, 2-4pm
$25 at the door, cash only
———
💘sisters,
i am so excited to share this with you... this event is not just another on the calendar; it marks the beginning of a much bigger dream… you know the kind of dream that feels like it is dreaming you? that. is. this...
.
shameless feminine is a new program and retreat series for women who are ready for their re-evolution— to be all woman, without a doubt and without apology, and... without a villain. shamelessly shameless are the women who are ready for the pendulum between the sexes to finally come to rest, to put down their sword and raise their light, to embody woman as mother once again. we are she.
.
each retreat will focus on a different superpower of the shameless feminine—from our intuitive emotions to our sacred sensuality—and will feature co-facilitators and healers who have inspired my personal journey and who will be sure to ignite yours.
.
i can"t wait! really, i can't...
though the program and retreat series are yet to launch (coming soon!), i couldn't resist the pull of my sisters. hearing your stories, feeling your pain, your call for healing—i knew i had to bring more to la than just a book and the promise of a program. #timeisup, and the medicine is needed now.
.
let’s heed the call together. 💘r
name: Rebecca Haywood
tweet_full:
ladies! join two of today's leading female shamans, rebecca haywood & tatyana rae von knobelsdorff, and unfold into the shameless feminine…
.
“we each have felt it. her yearning to release, to break open, to drink of her sorrow and sing of her rage. and we must. it is our unfolding— petals once held in shadow turning to the sun." ~rh .
.
rebecca & tatyana invite you into a sacred circle of women and into the unfolding... they will guide you into a shamanic dreaming process through which you will unfold into the organic wisdom of your feelings and allow them to move through you, to move you... closer, deeper, dissolved into their delicious invitation.
.
”we are designed to be obsessed with the calling heard within our hearts— constantly seeking to reunite with breath, as life, as divinity." ~tvk
.
where is the shameless feminine calling you?
.

text:
arms are for hugging and holding our hearts together as we grieve, adapt, and #elevate. who do you wish to hug right now? who can #hug you?

at the top of #decolonialbiznessworld are full #redlips that sing your unique #solutionstatements. yes, you! you have beautiful solutions to share! your full red lips can #mansplain away misogyny in business #leadership by being true love in the face of bulls**t and a total #bossbabe in the #csuite.

your red lips that sing solutions to issues like #climatechaos are held in the air by the #lovebirds of distribution and communication, which includes #marketing. 
once you’ve sung your solutions into existence, you exit and start anew.... a new venture, a new #business, a new adventure!

or, if you hit a block that you can't bypass or dismantle, you exit. living energy was made to flow freely. we need an exit from cycles of #trauma, namely #racism, capitalism, and #settlercolonialism. when you are able, you return to map your new path as a decolonial business #visionary. you don't need to be the #sacrifice. it is your sacred birthright to choose how you reckon with these times. you can #shinebrightlikeadiamond, not burn like one.

this method of business modeling encourages: #ascension and the #newearth.

yup, that’s right. this regenerative #medicinewheel aims for your spiritual #elevation and the financial and monetary success of your healing business. this world desperately needs your #brand of leadership. it needs you and #metoo. it needs the #starpeople and the #birdpeople with binoculars. it needs us to change the system from the inside out.

we work for love. that's a business imperative. love can be hard, fierce, relentless. and it can be as #sweet as water. #mniwiconi.

text:
kobe bryant removed from film festival jury after petition over 2003 rape allegation - blogged by: @raquelharristv
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#kobebryant won’t be able to attend a film festival because of his 2003 rape allegation.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
bryant was removed as a jury for the animation is film festival after people protested his attendance on change.org. the petition titled "remove sexual predator kobe bryant from 'animation is film' festival jury" was posted because of his rape allegation from 2003. the film festival will take place in los angeles this weekend.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
"after discussions with the various stakeholders of animation is film, the decision has been made to remove kobe bryant from the 2018 jury," said eric beckman, ceo of gkids, which produces the event. "we are a young organization and it is important to keep our collective energies focused on the films, the participating filmmakers, and our festival attendees." bryant would have respectively served, as he won an oscar in 2016 for his animation “dear basketball.” ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
an excerpt from the petition reads: "we, women and allies of the animation community demand that accused rapist and sexual predator kobe bryant be removed from the jury of animation is film festival. in light of the #metoo movement, there has been little to no recourse for kobe bryant’s actions of sexual assault. we demand that gkids, variety, & annecy revoke their complicity in enabling a sexual predator to continue a life without any accountability both as an individual and a celebrity. on its website 'animation is film' specifically states one of their primary purposes is to champion and support women filmmakers. it’s time to turn these words into action. it continued, “this is an urgent time to say no to toxic and violent behavior against women. for this reason, we ask that gkids, variety & ....…to read the rest log on to balleralert.com (clickable link on profile)

text:
one of the reasons i’ve long been a fan of craftivism, which is using handmade crafts as a form of activism, is the way it takes ordinary objects and subverts them in extraordinary ways. for me, the repurposing of found materials adds an environmental political piece that is also important to my work. while craftivism was founded as a slow intentional process often geared towards introverts as a way to gently protest, i like my art fast, furious and imperfect. i made these subversive little flags for my talk at the local @nationalnow chapter for love your body day last weekend using @snowmade’s paper stencil that you may have previously seen on my body (i’ll share some shots in stories.) i used bright pink spray paint on textile sample squares, and handful of them from a defunct interior design studio that i’ve held onto for years. add some silver clasp rings and voila - guerrilla art. you may just see a few around, boise. 👊🏼💖
.
.
.
.
.

text:
venus retrograde got me like 🔥🔥🔥
spinning, twisting, whirling, rolling
continuing down this path of unknowing
learning to breathe through suspension and uncertainty
letting go of addiction to security
constantly having energetic boundaries squeezed
being stretched past perceived maximum capacities 
desperation to inspiration, pain to peace
rage to creative expression
what is your body aching for? 
what does your soul need?
acknowledge and express moments of distress 
but lift yourself up and rise above conquest
engage with the psychological process
of birth, transformation, life, and death
sitting in darkness but feeling the light
within, around, burning ever so bright
gaining momentum to anchor deeper
courageously facing the secret keeper
dancing with betrayal, dishonesty, manipulation, fog, confusion
sharpening the sword and ability to cut through illusion
finding answers to riddles
remedies to deception and elusion
inner sight brings external mystery movies to a conclusion
clarity and vision give way to heightened decision
revelation arrives through patience and persistence
-soul on fire❤️vbk

text:
starting a new book is a risk, just like falling in love.
you have to commit to it. you open the pages knowing a little bit about it maybe, from the back or from a blurb on the front.
sometimes people advertise themselves as one thing and then when you get deep into it you realize that they’re something completely different.
you start off slow. the story is beginning to unfold. you’re unsure.

text:
“this is the first time i fully experienced and was affected by catcalling. i was nine, with my twelve year old sister and my mother. we were walking down the streets of san diego in the summer (so us children were wearing shorts). out of nowhere a truck full of men started screaming at the three of us “oooh i like chocolate! look at you walking down the street” and making kissing noises. to a mother and her two children.  my mom couldnt do anything without putting us in danger. so she just told us to ignore it.” - @shannon_corenthin

text: putting finishing touches on my latest piece, “a girl and her dog”. i’ve been in a total funk for months - unable to create at all. dealing with grief over a major loss for the last 6+ years as well as a lifetime of traumatic experiences i needed to process- has made me unable to produce like i did in the past and i finally feel like i’m coming out of that. trauma cuts synapses in our brains, and it can take time to regain our full functioning. especially as creatives, empaths, and spiritualists- there are a variety of hurdles which can get in our way- including but not limited to our own fears, depression, and spiritual messages from the other side we refuse to hear from people we refuse to let go of. this week i was inspired by my wee doggo who is getting on in years. i like to imagine in some reality he and i are in a forever loop of his favorite game with his favorite baseball. if you have suffered trauma, i want you to know that i am with you. i love you, i believed in you and full recovery is absolutely possible. #one day at a time. i love my pup! 😍 #doggo #alwaysmypupperdoodle #goodboy #fetch #art #artistsoninstagram #empath #healing #spiritworld #galaxies #finally #imagine #doggyheaven #atimeforeverything #ready #love #unconditional #forever #kind #brave #celestial #metoo #feminineenergy #beauty #survivor #life #light #hope #odefix

text:
dear fitness industry,

women are being sexually harassed and assaulted in and out of the gym -- and we need your help!

interested in helping? if so, we’ve created a free course just for you!

our national conversations are filled with sexual harassment and assault headlines.

hollywood. sports. politics. fitness.

it’s everywhere, and it’s not going away anytime soon.

our world (including our fitness world) is changing quickly, and it’s affecting our duties and responsibilities as coaches, trainers, health professionals, educators, and humans who care about helping other humans.

behavior that was once ignored, or “swept under the rug” is no longer being tolerated.

women are talking about it, reporting it, and publicly calling it out.

not being well-educated on sexual harassment means not only potentially harming women, but risking your reputation, and potentially much more.

i’m writing to you today to propose an incredibly powerful idea.

i’m asking you to make a personal commitment to join them in helping us create change.

not only will this free course help create a safer environment for women, but it’ll help keep you safe, too.

in this free 5-day course, you’ll learn:
.
💥 how to identify behavior that seems ok (but really isn’t).
💥 how to avoid common mistakes guys make (even when they think they “get it”).
💥 how to create a safe, welcoming environment for clients and patients.
💥 what you can do to stop harassment and assault in your gym and in the fitness industry.
💥 how you can be part of the solution, not the problem.

you’ll leave this course with a set of actionable tools and over a dozen downloadable resources including:
.
✔ a sample anti-harassment policy
✔ anti-harassment signage
✔ case studies for how to handle the most sensitive topics, including how to properly own up to a mistake if you make one
.
..and a clear path forward so you know exactly what to do (and what not to do). → get access now and start whenever you’re ready at the link in our bio.

on behalf of girls gone strong and millions of women around the world, thank you in advance for your support.

xoxo,
@themollygalbraith
cofounder and woman-in-charge at @thegirlsgonestrong

text:
hey everyone,
this is sean from ratemywinemaker.com.  i had the opportunity yesterday to speak to the vines to wines club and a wine business course at cal poly(my uni) about ratemywinemaker.com, about navigating life as a travelling winemaker, knowing your value, finding the right jobs for your goals, and taking the risks to make yourself uncomfortable. there are so many resources i could have used during my work travels to help maximize my access to good mentors and learning environments. 
ratemywinemaker.com will be releasing tons of new features and resources in the coming months to help you navigate your harvest travels. 
more than anything i just wanted to encourage the students to make the leap, because it all just started from wanting to make the most of my time with my best friends. 
and a big thank you to @cal_poly and @calpolyvinestowines for hosting ratemywinemaker.com!!

text:
each time i post about my past, i ask myself am i doing the right thing?
✨is this what god truly wants me to be doing with my life? am i going to regret this later?
✨i don’t truly know the answer to these questions
✨all i know is i am walking by faith and not by sight.
✨i am responding to that voice in my head that’s telling me “you have to let the world know and share your testimony of god’s grace, and love”.
✨............and how he saved my life....... .
.

text:
i love this picture of me. not like in a conceited way, but because of the story behind it. i had been in an emotionally abusive marriage with a husband who became physically violent when i said i wanted a divorce. .
▫
i knew there was no way he was going to let me leave without a fight, and i was afraid of it escalating because i had two small kids in the house. so i secretly started making plans to leave, then one day while he was at work i threw some clothes into a few bags, and made a run for it. .
▫
the next year was very rough. my ex harassed & threatened me constantly, refused to do anything for the kids, went on a smear campaign to spread lies about me to anyone who would listen, and deliberately ruined my credit as a way to "get even" with me for "breaking up the family". but i didn't let any of that stop me. i worked hard, took care of my kids, and stayed focused on my goals. .
▫
when this picture was taken, i had just got hired for my very first job as a certified teacher & i was waiting for the train to take me to brooklyn, ny where i would start a new job as well as a new life for myself and my kids. that's why i love this picture; because to me it represents my strength, courage, independence, happiness, and the will to succeed... all the things i rediscovered within myself after i decided to escape the abuse. .
▫
thanks for reading my story. i sincerely hope other people in toxic relationships will learn from it & find the strength to leave. 💜
.
angela davis-moss
founder of nah b, inc.
.

text:
i dont tell people to love yourself because it sounds good to be like " yea, i love me".... many people speak through their ego when they say i love myself.... when you love yourself there is no war within you.. so you dont have to worry about war without... in the exterior world... i'm not saying people and life wont test you but what i am saying is when you love yourself...you have peace in your heart.... therefore whatever may come before you.... you will be rooted in peace. because that's who you are... so you will remain centered ....but when you operate through the ego. you do not love yourself .. you love an image you created for yourself that constantly needs reassurance... you will be vulnerable, envious... etc. and constantly battling negative thoughts in your head ... when there is a fight within... you will always find yourself fighting the world... dont believe me about yourself or possibly "them"? pay attention to the fruits? what does it bare? is it a world of chaos? or peace? does it give you energy or does it drain you?
dont let the world tell you who you are... love yourself know yourself. change yourself within... change your world without #letsheal #metoo #kwkemetic444centerofherbalhealing

text:
🔊 #pathetic #entitled #parasite — #donaldtrump defended his treatment of christine blasey ford, the woman who accused now-supreme court justice brett kavanaugh of sexual misconduct, saying that the judge would never been confirmed:
-
“had i not made that speech, we would not have won,” trump told ’60 minutes’ host lesley stahl in a sweeping interview that aired sunday. “i was just saying she didn’t seem to know anything.”
-
#trump openly questioned ford’s claims and mocked the broader #metoo movement during a rally in mississippi, just days after she gave emotional testimony about her allegations before the senate judiciary committee. ford alleged that a “stumbling drunk” kavanaugh sexually assaulted her when they were both teenagers at a party in the 1980s, pinning her to a bed and attempting to remove her clothing.
-
the judge vehemently denied the allegations, including those from two other woman who publicly came forward with similar accounts of sexual misconduct. he was confirmed earlier this month in a slim 50-48 vote.
-
stahl asked several times if the president had to make fun of and mimic ford, but trump claimed that he didn’t do so and said supporters at his rally who laughed at his remarks could do what they liked.
-
“i think she was treated with great respect,” trump said of ford. when stahl pushed him on his remarks, he shot back:
-
“you know what?” trump countered, “i’m not gonna get into it because we won. it doesn’t matter. we won.”
-
during the rally, trump lambasted ford’s recollection of the event, alluding that because she couldn’t remember the exact address of the party, she couldn’t positively identify the man who assaulted her. ford said she was “100 percent” certain it was kavanaugh who held her down.
-
″“i had one beer, right? i had one beer! how did you get home? i don’t remember. how’d you get there? i don’t remember. where’s the place? i don’t remember,” trump mocked. “upstairs, downstairs, i don’t know. but i had one beer. that’s the only thing i remember.”
—
#stablegenius #greed #hypocrisy #historyrepeats #womenempowerment #misogyny #sexism #accountability #educate #bias #dumptrump #fucktrump #predator #60minutes

text:
#metoo "in october 2017 many women posted #metoo on their social media to show how many women had been subjected to and experienced sexual harassment, assault and abuse.
it was a movement that spread awareness for many. it brought about change and begun advocacy for women everywhere. it brought light to a problem that needed to be addressed. it was something that i’m not only glad happened but recognize the need that it had to happen.

here’s the thing.

i stayed silent....."
.
.
new blog post is up, it wasn't an easy one, but i felt like it had to be said.
.
.
.
.
.
#womensrights #respect #love #boyswillbegoodhumans #men #women #equality #change #society #survivor #isurvived

text:
#whyerc wednesday from our program coordinator, erica: “i want to exert my right to be free as much as i want others to have that same experience. i want people to feel free to be themselves without being shamed for it, without being assaulted for it, without being afraid. at multiple points in my life i did not feel free, i felt scared and ashamed. i didn’t have full control of my body and i felt lost because i did not know how to say no. i did not know that i could say no. & i didn’t know how to deal with the negativity that resulted from that and so i sat with it in silence. thanks to erc i am now on the right track to healing and overcoming experience that marked me. 
i am so grateful that i want to give back and help other people find their way to healing and i think that the work erc does, does just that.”

text: a few lines from “parts.” - my 2nd book of poetry, the hurting, is now available at the very affordable price of $20.  link in bio.  it’s a one time run - so, get a copy for yourself if you’re a fan of my work.  your support helps me to continue to create.  thank you. 🌿  sometimes, as an artist, you have to do what makes you the most uncomfortable.  you have to push yourself further - beyond the comfortable spaces you’ve learned to create in.  poetry is relatively new to me.  it only really became a way with which i could express myself when my mental health got so bad that i couldn’t bring myself to sing.  creating and releasing this work has been one of the most challenging experiences in my personal development.  i came face to face with monsters and memories i’d been burying for years.  i have found there are less boundaries in poetry.  i gave the little boy inside me that i tried so desperately to forget a voice.  and now, i’m giving these stories to the world because survivors of abuse sometimes need something tangible they can relate to.  experiences that remind them they aren’t alone in how their body, mind and spirit remember pain.  buy this book for yourself and then give it to someone you know who needs it.  my hope is that it becomes one of those books.  passed between friends, lovers and survivors as a means to connect and heal. in these poems, i share a lot about how sexual abuse and childhood exploitation impacts me as an adult.  these sometimes difficult topics are pristinely illustrated by the very talented @michaeljhildebrand.  michael - thank you for doing all the work you did on this project with me.  you held the very delicate parts of my trauma and my past and treated them with such care.  i love you.  this is “the hurting.” •  #authorsofinstagram #bookstagram #poet #poetsofinsta #poets #poem #poems #poetry #poetryinmotion #poetrybook #goodreads #bookworm #bookclub #wordshurt #relationshipquotes #heartbreakquotes #heartbrokenquotes #heartbroken #heartbreak #spilledink #writerslife #writingcommunity #writersoninstagram #writersofig #quotesaboutlove #quotesaboutlife #poetsofig #writer #prose #metoo

text:
it’s ok to talk about your sexy: it is important to learn to talk about your feelings at an early age.  talking about your feelings can help you stay in good mental health and deal with times when you feel troubled. talking about your feelings isn’t a sign of weakness. it’s part of taking charge of your wellbeing and doing what you can to stay healthy.
talking can be a way to cope with a problem you’ve been carrying around in your head for a while. just being listened to can help you feel supported and less alone. and it works both ways. if you open up, it might encourage others to do the same.
it’s not always easy to describe how you’re feeling. if you can’t think of one word, use lots. what does it feel like inside your head? what does it make you feel like doing?
you don't need to sit your loved ones down for a big conversation about your wellbeing. many people feel more comfortable when these conversations develop naturally - maybe when you're doing something together. if it feels awkward at first, give it time. make talking about your feelings something that you do. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
i recently worked a couple of high school homecomings with dj j-element and they were amazing, especially because j-element is truly a master at that craft of djing. he knows how to play the right songs at the right times in order to keep the crowd engaged at all times. 
the energy, the excitement, the enthusiasm was exhilarating at each party. i love it but there is one thing about the current pop culture that i would like to see changed and that is the messages of the lyrics. 
as the #metoo movement is gaining momentum, i hope we also examine how the sexual messages of popular songs might be contributing to the rape culture. i hope we start to pay more attention and start to hold music artists more accountable for the messages that they are sending out to kids because, really, if you read the lyrics of the songs that are the most popular right now, you will see that many of them are promoting messages of sexual promiscuity and the objectification of women. 
fortunately, i think a lot of teenagers are just focused on having fun and not really paying attention to the song lyrics. however, i do believe that subconsciously, the attitudes and the themes of these song lyrics are influencing our mindsets.

what do you think?

text: this fall i have the privilege of spending saturdays with @ggm_chi and @tobieloomis in a classroom downtown at @afterschoolmatters with 17 lovely young women - all high school students. after interning with them after my freshman year of college and although i was tasked with helping run the program and instruct the young women participating in the program, i found this to be one of the first instances where i was able to inch out of the bubble i’d grown up in, as well as the ivy league “utopia” i’d been groomed to desire, and really learn about the city i claimed to be from. empowerment through #medialiteracy is of course a focus, but what fosters a mutual learning between all of us is the discussions we have and the experiences and opinions we share with one another. this is something we filmed on our first day... their fire from a young age inspires me to keep moving toward my goals and i hope we can inspire them to use keep their voices despite what our the country’s most powerful tell us, despite being underrepresented minorities and despite who people have decided deserve representation. @global_girl_media @womens_voices_now @huffpostwomen #women#girlpower#womenempowerment#listen#her#voice#believeher#metoo#video#share

text:
think you could give up sex (yes that includes masterbation) for an entire week? we gave it a shot and journaled about it as part of an experiment in sexual transmutation. can you really channel your sexual energy into success? we thought it would be easy since i just broke up with metal dick, and @arielsnotamermaid is picky af. but let’s just say there were a few curveballs after a date with multiple bracelet guy... did either of us survive the week? listen to find out!

then, we are joined by comedian @davidkoechner who helps us break down the saga of chris and kandi, and how we saved the day after a phone call with her screaming boyfriend led to a radio prank gone-wrong. koechner also helps us discuss social responsibility in dating, how the #metoo movement affects relationships between men and women, and how he views dating in 2018 as he watches and advises his kids while they navigate the tricky terrain.
.
all on this episode of @ghostedhunters on @itunes @spotify @googleplaymusic.
.

text:
indian minister mj akbar won’t quit over #metoo

indian union minister mj akbar on sunday dodged calls for his resignation and said allegations of sexual harassment against him were “false, fabricated and deeply distressing”. minister
linking the allegations to elections ahead, mj akbar also threatened legal action against his accusers. sources say the government has “nothing to do with the accusations” against him and his stepping down may “set a bad precedent”.
mr akbar, 67, was on an official tour in nigeria when nearly a dozen women came out with detailed accounts of his alleged sexual misconduct as part of a thread on social media that has snowballed into a #metoo movement in india, ndtv reports.

why has this storm risen a few months before a general election? is there an agenda? you be the judge. these false, baseless and wild allegations have caused irreparable damage to my reputation and goodwill… this is deeply distressing. i will be taking appropriate legal action,” mr akbar said.minister
mr akbar, who headed prominent newspapers like the telegraph and the asian age, has been accused of harassing younger women, especially newcomers. some alleged that he would call women to his hotel room for job interviews. others said he behaved inappropriately behind closed doors of his office.minister
the accusations started pouring in after journalist priya ramani tweeted on october 8 that mr akbar was the man she had referred to in an incident she shared in a magazine article a year ago, when the harvey weinstein scandal in the us triggered the #metoo movement.
besides ms ramani, the women who spoke out against mj akbar include prerna singh bindra, ghazala wahab, shutapa paul, anju bharti, suparna sharma, shuma raha, malini bhupta, kanika gahlout, kadambari m wade, majlie de puy kamp and ruth david.

text: moira donegan, creator of the shitty media men list, is being sued by one of the men mentioned in the file for $1.5 million in libel damages. the shitty media men list had for intention to collect sexual harassment and abuse allegations so women in journalism and publishing could warn each other about potential predators. over the course of its google circulation, 70 men were accused, of them stephen elliott founder at rumpus, who allegedly engaged in sexual harassment, coercion, and sexual assault. “i only wanted to create a place for women to share their stories of harassment and assault without being needlessly discredited or judged,” donegan explains. to offset the lawsuit, she launched a gofundme, which is currently at $100,000 out of a $500,000 goal. tap link in bio for more feminist news!

・・・
beautiful early morning breakie at cornwall children’s treatment centre! today honourable guests were lisa mcleod , minister of children community and social services and guest speaker us olympian  margaret hoelzer from huntsville alabama. her story was around being sexually abused from the age 5 to 7. her story was about telling her story to someone, she trusted and the person believing them; her story was about being from a victim to a survivor. her story was about resiliency. 
in the era of #metoo movement - trusting to speak up is heart wrenching. so when someone states and tells you their story - believe them. the battle from victim to survivor becomes half the battle.

thank to my hometown for creating a safe place for children disclosing about their sexual abuse story.

text:
having a bad day? you are strong. wish you belonged to a community? you have sisters. wanting both? #sisterstrong is a community of women that exists with the sole purpose of encouraging women everywhere, in every stage of life.
.
i can vividly picture the moment my life reached a crossroads: i was a sophomore in college, crying in the shower at my sorority and pleading with my body to let me sleep for the first time in weeks since being assaulted.  i remember thinking to myself, “why can’t i be stronger? i feel like i have no support, not even from my sisters.”
.
that’s when it hit me: sisterhood doesn’t have to be dictated by blood or memberships.
.
for the past few years, i’ve played with an idea. minoring in nonprofit leadership, i utilized my education to learn about starting my own organization. i reached out to countless people, auditioned to speak at tedxgrand forks, but the timing was never right. also, i was a broke (and broken!) college student without the energy or resources to help others in the capacity i wanted to.
.
today, four years later, i know this idea placed was on my heart for a reason. although i hope this movement becomes more than a hashtag, i need to start somewhere! so, sisters, i ask for your support of my dream posting this hashtag to uplift, inspire, and connect with sisters everywhere.
.
you may feel weak; but with the support of your sisters, you can be #sisterstrong
💪🏻💪🏼💪🏽💪🏾💪🏿
