text:
new trainers!!! ... now that's how you cheer this girl up. ♀‍🏃🏻💪🏻💗
the main reason i started running is that if i ever find myself in a difficult situation again i want to feel like i have the ability to run away. when it came down to it fright and freeze seemed to overtake flight. so when i complain i'm too slow and not getting any faster, that's what i'm thinking of. so its really not helpful when people tell me it's not about speed, or competing against others. for me they're wrong, even though i don't want to win races, i want to be able to save myself if necessary. i hope i never again need to obviously, but if it came to it, i want to be able to outrun any assailant. why does this even have to be such a consideration
😭

text:
whether or not you grew up in a culturally religious home, there is no denying that the way we think about spirituality as adults impacts the way we treat each other in our marriages.

in the latest episode of the #staymarried podcast (s4 ep5) we unpack a question from rachel submitted to ask #staymarried. she’s concerned that her husband shawn, who once attended church with her regularly, would now prefer to spend his sundays hunting and fishing. she asked us if we have advice on how to “get him to come to church” with her. we address that, as well as our own perspective on our current “church shopping” journey.

you can find links to resources as well as the full episode at the link in our profile. you can also listen on apple podcasts, #spotify, or wherever you listen to your favorite shows.

#linkinprofile goes to https://staymarriedblog.com/church-shopping-or-nah/
#churchtoo #metoo #emptythepews #churchclarity #clarityisreasonable 
enjoy!

text:
guess where i am going to be this saturday? @theunspokenbellefoundation  is having a costume gala to take a stand against abuse against women and children, and i am proud to be one of their vendors in that event. it’s a great cause, and right now, it’s the perfect time to make our voices heard about those issues that are ruining so many lives. 
someone wisely stated: “it’s easier to build strong children, than to repair broken adults.” and when i first started this page, i told my followers, i didn’t want to be another pretty face selling them nice items. i wanted to find a way to be involved through my business and give back to my community, and this is why i take those type of events at heart. so if you are in the palm beach, boynton, boca raton, fort lauderdale areas, please come support them and come say hi to me, and if you are an emma’s world treasures followers, you get a free gift. but don’t tell the others attendees😉

#stopabuseagainstwomen #stopwomenabuse #stopchildabuse #metoomovement #metoo #bocaraton #delraybeach #boyntonbeach #westpalmbeach #palmbeach #lakeworth #deerfieldbeach #fortlauderdale #pompanobeach

text:
wasn’t that rainbow insanely beautiful? but it’s back to work. 
four custom xizozu anthem pendants on the work bench now. two for a two sisters who lost their mom, one for a us military vet living a worthwhile life while dealing with ptsd and the last, a woman who manages to thrive and be successful while balancing mental illness. it’s when i create xizozu like these that i have to stop and marvel at all the strong, strong, strong people on this planet. and give thanks that i can contribute in a small way to their incredible journeys.

text:
domestic violence awareness hasn’t caught up with #metoo. here’s why.

when kaylee kapatos posted on facebook this month that she was a survivor of domestic violence, using the hashtag #whyistayed, the response among her friends was muted.

only the week before, she had posted about sexual assault with the hashtag #whyididntreport and got what she called “overwhelmingly positive feedback.” “it’s totally different,” said ms. kapatos, 25, who works as a residence life coordinator at michigan technological university. “people just don’t want to talk about it.” over the past year, the #metoo movement has transformed culture, in many ways expanding beyond sexual assault and harassment to become a transcendent force for empowering women. there have been discussions about what it’s like for women to go on bad dates, how women must calculate the risk of mundane tasks like selling an item online or going on a run, and why it’s important to believe women when they tell their stories.
tonielaw#stopdomesticviolence #justicefortonie#breakthecycle#iamatonie#yhroughtonieweheal🙏

text:
truth talk: these last few years have felt like a never-ending onslaught of challenging and triggering events in which we, as women, are ignored, abused, told we don’t matter as human beings, and that if we knew what was good for us we’d stay silent. i wake up some mornings feeling completely battered and bruised, betrayed, angry, and worst of all… powerless.
.
this is when i reach for #chrysocolla, a stone of empowerment for the feminine divine, the goddesses and wise women in us all. it teaches us that as long as we continue to raise our voices, we are invincible… that true power lies in our ability to never stop expressing our truth, and to find compassion for those that are afraid of our strength. chrysocolla is stone of forgiveness, allowing us to release the poison that is holding us back, to strengthen emotional bonds with each other and help us form the human collective we are moving towards. it’s also pretty great at reducing menstrual pain, pms, and conducive to easy pregnancies/birth, so that's a bonus.🤰
.
just try to remember when you’re feeling angry or helpless: every time it feels like a defeat, we are pushing forward against thousands of years of indoctrination, but these are the violent death throes of those who wish us to stay silent. the #metoo movement could not have happened one hundred years ago. women weren’t allowed to open credit cards or bank accounts without their husband’s permission 35 years ago. dr ford would not have been able to give that testimony in front of a room full of men even 10 years ago.
.
we are being heard. that’s what has them running scared.😘

➰
you are you and you're beautiful and worthy and important and enough no matter what!! you don't need to be fixed, cured, manipulated, or changed. that happened to be my affirmation today.
➰ 
stay in the love and the light. see the beauty in yourself, in others, in the world around you.

text: last sunday @agouldini and i saw @minghearts #usualgirls directed by @tynerafaeli @roundaboutnyc. look at @djgramps! i simply adore this wonderful human. what a bizarre experience to watch this lovely man act out the villain in what felt like some of my worst and most traumatic childhood experiences (he’s scarily good). this show did something i personally have never experienced in this way. i felt like i was watching my own memories play out in front of me. the way it captures those specific moments that shape and change us. what it means to be a girl. a young woman. specifically an #asianamerican girl/woman. girls are weird and wonderful and mean and gross and funny and real and raw and vulnerable and strong. all of the things. 💖@midoriglory is nothing short of a superhero. i bow down, gurl. what you do is masterful. @jlimster you are legend and broke my heart into a thousand pieces. 💖one thing people don’t really talk about when they talk about asians in regards to #representationmatters is when you’re a minority and you never see yourself at all you also never see the bad things. you never see people who look like you go through trauma or deal with huge things because people like you rarely get to feel and experience a plot things. and not knowing that others like you are struggling and have been there too can be very lonely and isolating. i left the theater that day almost dazed. i had never been shown back any semblance of the pain i experienced in this specific way. it’s weird. i know how important theater and storytelling is to understanding ourselves and this show has given me the bittersweet gift of looking outside to see inside. my mirror. and oddly it also made me feel ferocious by the end. when i think of the daily challenges - bullshit - we as women - as women of color - experience every single fucking day since we could walk and talk i believe our strength in unparalleled. just to walk down a street. just to stand. just to exist. i am in awe. we have been fucked since the beginning and #stillwerise #thatsit #exactlythat #itsallreal #thatswhathappens #metoo

text:
stop telling girls & teach boys
⛔
you know... its really sad to think that non of us are safe...not at home, not in schools, churches, malls, police stations, hospitals... no place on earth seems to be safe.

you know i remember when i was still a kid i'd hear elders say things  to little girls like... "sit properly in front of your uncles... sit properly can't you see there are men... close your legs there are men in the house... dress properly there are men in the house"... as a kid i didn't see anything wrong with it. it was a norm. something told to every girl and expected of them.

today... i am filled with so much disappointment as i recall the 'sit properly there are men in the house'.. thinking that those men referred to were our uncles, our brothers, our fathers, our grandfathers, our pastors, our teachers and more... it makes me ask myself 'were we living with monsters?'. so a little girl or your daughter, niece, must learn to close her legs or 'sit properly' or 'dress properly' because  you, her father, her teacher, uncle or brother is around??? the world has really taught us to be careful... it has taught women to fix themselves for men, it has taught us to be safe.. to act safe.. but in doing so, it has taught men to be those monsters we were trying to avoid. 
if you think that women are raped because of how they dress... then what about women who still get raped when fully covered, head to toe!?? think about kids who get raped. think about babies who get raped... what if it was your sister, mother or your daughter.

there's no excuse for rape. shame on you for even trying to come up with one.

a woman can walk around butt naked and raping her will still not be justifiable... because there isn't any excuse. none!!! you are a rapist because you choose to be a rapist. enough with excuses. enough with defending rapists.
enough with teaching females to be safe instead of educating males to not rape or assault. 
and yes we will keep making "noise" each time one of us becomes a victim till there are no more cries. may many silent victims find the courage to speak up like #cherylzondi did.
#timesup

text:
in response- from a fellow (female) designer. 
i think hedi slimane is coming under totally unnecessary scrutiny. as designers (female or male) we have one task and one objective- to make women feel great. that’s it - it really is that simple. 
yes there is creative interpretation and each designer has their own ‘handwriting’ and way of conveying this. however our only aim in real terms is to create pieces that women love, not for anyone but themselves. garments that they feel fantastic in, whatever the event. not for the gaze of men, not for the approval of other women. just for themselves. that’s it. our entire job is to make women (of every age, size, and ethnicity) walk out of the door feeling amazing, confident and stylish. to allow them to go about their day almost forgetting what they are actually wearing because they are at ease, confident in themselves and comfortable. 
do you know what? i personally take great pride in achieving that for my customers. i think hedi’s comment about ‘so is it not ok for women to wear mini skirts?!’ is totally founded. why shouldn’t we?? women regardless of age should feel free to wear what they choose and feel comfortable in, free from the unsolicited opinions of anyone. not for anyone else, just for them. 
personally i dress for me. if someone (female or male) sends me compliment, great - it’s always nice to hear that a colour / shape really suits me and i’ll take it with thanks. however am i going to spit my dummy or change my appearance to please others of either gender? that would be a no. never. not happening.

text:
i haven’t yet told my #metoo and #whyididntreport stories publicly, but i wanted to share a #ptsdandme moment.
.
living with ptsd due to experiencing sexual and gender based violence can be very difficult at times. like many survivors, i’m sometimes triggered or thrown off by an unexpected movie scene, a comment from a well-meaning close friend, or even a certain smell.
.
during my lunch break i saw a man who looked eerily like the person who assaulted me while i was at the @utknoxville. this fella continued walking behind me for several minutes, even though i let him pass me a time or two, and i barely made it to the corner of my street without my heart jumping out of my chest.
.
frank and regina, two endearing neighbors who live in the house across the street of mine (we originally met because of my puppy, daisy, of course), happened to be walking in my direction and saw me; and the panicked look on my face. i didn’t know how to describe what i was feeling or thinking in german, other than “i was frightened by a man”. frank calmly took me by the arm and walked me to the door of my house, he asked if i needed anything or if he should call the police. i smiled and declined his supportive gesture. i don’t know him well, and didn’t have the capacity to offer him a hug, but i believe he knew i was grateful for his kindness and empathy.
.
yes, as survivors we have lived through certain experiences, but life is about so much more than just surviving. sometimes we become victims again, because the trauma resurfaces when we least expect it; no matter how many years since the incident(s) happened or how many times we’ve talked about them, either in therapy or with those closest to us.
.
i’m learning to be gentle with myself, to open up to my loved ones, to not feel guilty about trying to seek balance and rest when i need to. to all the “survictims” out there, be gentle with yourself: laugh, live, cry, rest, repeat. ❤️

text:
spending most of the day at the boston municipal courthouse, has been eye opening. 
a little over a year ago, i was sexually assaulted on the subway, while working with my two littlest guys. i wrote here, and on fb about that incident, and subsequent reaction of the 2 year old in my care. 
today, i sat in court to testify against the man arrested immediately after i filed the report with the police. so of course, today i brought along the books #tattoosontheheart , and #theyamasandniyamas, to keep me company in the phonesless court, and to remind me that compassion is always what i want to lead with. always. 
but that’s not easy, especially when i feel you’ve threatened the well being of children, children i love. so i needed reminders today, just a few giant shoves in the right direction while i waited. 
and waited! plenty of cases came and went while mine sat untouched, because he was in custody, and hadn’t arrived yet. i was the 2nd person in the room, the first being the ada that opened the door at 8:20 am. it wasn’t that i was bright eyed and bushy tailed to do this. i was fairly anxious in all honesty. i just wanted to be a good witness, one who wouldn’t be doubted. i thought timeliness and the right clothes might help to that end. and i was hoping i could hop back in time to be of some use to my bosses, who have been very supportive of me through this entire process. 
while i sat, rather uncomfortably, and read/listened to the petty crimes and pleas roll by; i had many opportunities to practice compassion. for the criminal accused of a crime in a language he doesn’t speak, to the stressed out courtroom intern who hadn’t quite mastered the art of talking to the judge while simultaneously reading the file seemingly for the first time. there was compassion for a returning prosecutor who was just on his legs after major surgery. definitely for the prisoners who came in, unwashed and in shackles; especially when compared to the rest of the corporate attire in the room. 
but when i saw him, i felt anxious, not unable to breathe anxious; just slightly uncomfortable. and i was relieved. because of all the people i held in compassion today, (see comments)

text:
new video: "orpheus", recorded at rehearsal.  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mjgg9z0rxu0 [j]: "i wrote this after seeing men on pedestals get excused for their actions while they hid behind the "but i'm a good guy, look at my friends!" and giving lip service to the struggle of survivors to cover themselves.

this song was inspired by the actions of aziz ansari and louis c.k., men who get forgiven and applauded after "bravely" returning while the women and communities they hurt are still reeling. it was perps in my own community and the survivors finding their voices.

orpheus was a golden boy, and his charming tunes keep us locked into not seeing what's happening. the consummate performer...who is eventually destroyed by maenads. there's definitely fury, and we're only getting louder.

enjoy orpheus. #metoo "

#nerdmusic #maenads

text:
on the climate change of the me too movement, after seeing many comments offending these women for coming out after all these years of hiding what happened to them because this world would try to shame them, saying they “wanted it” or they should have “dressed better” or “should have left before it got out of hand” it’s really sad how some people think, like why try to make excuses for what these individuals did to these ladies? why? the people who used their position to abuse others for their own unnecessary wants. i believe we as men should educate the other men how to properly treat women. if you have kids please show them how to treat women because they’re queens and should all be treated as such and that if a woman says no they shouldn’t get upset and should simply move on with their life. maybe if we educate these men, these women wouldn’t have to walk down a street looking over their shoulder because a predator could be right around the corner.
📸 @doseofadreamer

i don't get it... why the nature of people .......for further www.myjoopress.wordpress.com ￼

i don't get it... why the nature of people got to change when they are with friends of opposite sex, may be its human nature, both get their behavior changed when they are with that friend and after that they come back from this fake reality, it's been a good technique to feel special among other friends, fight ,extra care for that person ,good . but why you can't be that person all the time? it's that ,you might show extra respect for that person but deep you are away from your reality. these days i am feeling how our society divided us as boys and girls, you can't be seen with your friend with opposite sex in public. yes, it is just in urban and middle class families. but yet true.

parents might think dividing our communities like this is the best solution for all, it's been so long living like this. but i think this is the main cause why boys get in bad influence, overthinking to possess girls, and girls get addicted to hide their feelings. if boys had a few of girl friends, who they trust ,they won't a have a thinking of abusing girls for their dress or character,they could learn to respect and gain a good charm in society. if girls had not to hide any such thing ,they could gain all the mastery they need to express their creativity on a big scale. yet i thank all those parents who are trying to remove this barrier. but this society.... which is nothing else than us, created by us, became a mislead . couple dance is bad,go solo ,you don't need a partner,good. but why hesitate to ask for help,ask for opinion.

together we can learn many new things,which we can only if we share our thoughts. girl's artistic and boy's managements .... remember jab we met,band baaja barat and yeh jawani hai diwani now you think have you got to married , no ,look at ae dil hai mushkil .i mean to say don't go the wrong way just see how they enhanced each others personality. get over it ya... how long .

text: today’s musing: in my household we support and empower women. all women, of every color, creed, orientation, and religious affiliation. in my household we do not stand for children to be ripped apart from their parents or left to fight for themselves in court at just 3 years old. in my household we fight for lgbtq+ rights and we won’t stand for the abuse of anyone in the community. in my household we love the lord, we value his teachings and we do not use biblical texts as a form of harassment or belittlement. in my household we believe in love above all else; even in the face of oppression, disagreement, and bold-faced anger. we also vote. so go vote and let’s make some waves. (@artofbeinglo has nothing to do with this post other than she’s a strong, independent, fierce and talented woman that i adore)

text: this weekend my daughter turned 12.  this is me at the same age.  i had already kissed a few boys, been grabbed on the butt and was extremely self conscious about being “pretty enough.” my parents didn’t tell me anything about boys, sex, puberty or love, i had to learn it on my own.  as i reflect back, i was looking for it at this age.  i wanted the attention, and beauty was one of the primary ways to find it.  i’ve grown up and learned a lot about myself, and that desire has changed.  but it opened doors for boys to say and do things i wasn’t so comfortable with.  this is why i am open and honest with my daughter (and age appropriate). i am a sex positive therapist because we can’t deny that natural part of ourself.  i welcome people to have a positive relationship with it, so it can manifest joy, pleasure, intimacy and self awareness, rather than being misunderstood or afraid of it.  question: what part of your sexuality is challenging to accept?  let’s talk about it!  #talkaboutsex #openminded #ibelieveher #ibelievesurvivors #metoo #healthysex #healthysexual #beyourself #shareyourstory #survivor #loveheals #womensmarch

text: i have to write on this more at length, especially since it is now clear because of how it was handled it is one of the few successes of the #metoo⁠ ⁠movement, but today marks the one year anniversary of chris savino’s history of sexual harassment being made public. much as with skyler page and “clarence”, both “the loud house” and the animation industry as a whole are far better off without him. buzzfeed news’s first-hand article remains the best report about how the investigation and union trial proceeded. although part of me wonders why this is one of the few #metoo⁠ investigations which actually succeeded, part of me also realizes it’s due to the bravery and determination of cheyenne curtis, megan nicole dong, jessie juwono, and others who intentionally went through the animation guild to find a fitting punishment for a situation where they felt, as one of those involved put it in the article, “‘i’m sorry’ is not enough”. to the power of strength in numbers and unions and to female animators everywhere fighting for a safer and kinder work environment. (artwork by rachell sumpter for buzzfeed news)

text:
and yes, it’s from the the help.  it’s also something i have my daughter repeat to her self right before i drop her off at school. .
.
the other day i picked her up from school and she was in tears because she got the results from her physical fitness exam in which she failed -not enough push-ups, pull-ups, not a fast enough mile, blah, blah blah.  but that’s not what got me heated.  turns out they reported her bmi (body mass index) and hers indicated that she was over weight. .
.
so i start telling her that she is beautiful, that all women have different body types and their all beautiful.  i tell her that this society we live in is sick and has created these unrealistic expectations of what a woman’s body should look like.  i tell her we live in a society that objectifies women’s bodies, creates body image issues, and contributes to making young girls feel insecure, low self-esteem, and just feel bad about their bodies in general.  we have this real-talk for like an hour and maybe i even played christina aguilera’s “beautiful” several times on repeat because...the song just works 🤷🏽‍♂️. .
.
i’m woke to the issues around childhood obesity (the reason the cdc issued the physical exam) & i’m woke to the importance of living and encouraging a healthy lifestyle but the importance should be for her to feel healthy, not on what she looks like.  what i wasn’t woke to was the fact that women have been dealing with this their whole lives.  i can’t imagine how awful this must be for all y’all to live in a world that treats you like this, that makes you feel not pretty enough, not curvy enough, not skinny enough...not enough. please believe me when i tell you...you are very much enough.  all women are beautiful.  i’m just sorry we live in a world that can’t see it. 👸🏽🙌🏾💜✊🏽 (ps sorry for the long post). ok i’m done.✌🏾
.
.

#repost @united.hindu.official with @get_repost
・・・
सोशल मीडिया के द्वारा मुज़्ज़्मल सईद ने एक हिन्दू मॉडल को प्यार के जाल में फंसा दिया, फिर घर बुला कर उस 'काफ़िर लड़की' को मुल्लो के सामने परोस दिया जाता है। जब वह मना करती है तो उसका गैंगरेप कर उसा गला काट कर बैग में पैक कर फेक दिया जाता है। क्या कभी ऐसी वारदात करते हुए किसी शांतिदूत की किसी मुस्लिम लड़की के साथ करते देखा है? नही यही तो है जिहाद 'काफ़िर' का रेप करो उसे मारो या बेच दो या 10 बच्चे पैदा कर के छोड़ दो। अब कहा मर गया वो गांडू सेकुलरिज़्म? 
इस घटना की कोई प्राइम टाइम कवरेज नही, इस पर कोई अवार्ड वापसी नही इस पर कोई बॉलीवुड वाला प्लेकार्ड ले कर सामने आयेगा। इसको तो #metoo कैम्पेन चलाने का मौका भी न मिला। अब कहा मर गया वो सेकुलरिज्म?

text: i wanted to take this with a professional photographer with a personal, exposed session. but i need to share this - especially with our current political and social issues. everyone’s healing from their past is different. i can talk about my assaulters easily now because i forgave them the way jesus forgave. i will never forget what they did though. this tattoo session had the most emotional ending and i am happy that @thegreasereaper was part of my journey. he respected everything this symbol means to me and other sexual assault/rape survivors. it is simple but my story is forever out in the open. i still have nightmares, internally cringe when someone touches me, have a hard time trusting new men i potentially want to date - which leads to my forever singleness. i didn’t ask for these things... you took away my old normalness and my new normal is still hard to live with after 6+ years. those men may have broken me, but the love of jesus and men that truly respect women have helped heal me. @hillsongworship thank you for writing a song that spoke to me and lead me to christ. @ladygaga @lostconversations thank you for helping me heal. #iamasurvivor #believesurvivors

text:
finding the freedom to love yourself is hard in a society that teaches us to only see our imperfections. 
in a society that says to hide our bodies or we are lacking self respect, to cover up as to not entice being touched in an unwanted way, to dress modestly or you are a slut however if you dress modestly you are a prude. 
it’s an internal battle of the voice that’s telling you every inch that you shouldn’t love or show, and always wanting to change it just enough to find the happy. 
the freedom to love doesn’t come from any kg you’ve lost, any surgery you’ve undergone, any clothing you’re covering or uncovering with... that love comes from within from honouring your fucking amazing body every single day every damn inch of it.

text:
pia camil’s “bara bara bara” approximates the makeshift tented markets of latin american urban landscapes and occupied the heart of fair market. in an entirely new configuration from its previous iterations. the work is created by sewing together hundreds of used t-shirts that have made their ways back and forth across the us/ mexico border—arriving for sale in las torres market in iztapalapa, a neighborhood of mexico city, to be bought and integrated into this artwork which has now traveled over much of the united states. the apparel utilized in this work reminds of the way that text-based messaging and slogans transmit ideas across borders to become absorbed within cultural manifestations.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
last december during miami art week, @anthony_spinello and @zoelukov curated the first in a series of alternative art fairs, entitled “fair.” fair., an alternative non-commercial art fair that took place december 7-10, 2017 at brickell city centre, served as a platform for a diverse and multigenerational group of women artists. fair. seeked to address gender inequality in the art world and beyond by providing space for radical women artists to create site-specific interventions in a non-traditional venue.

fair. was generously supported by swire properties inc, in partnership with the john s. and james l. knight foundation.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
photo: diana larrea / @parcialmentenublada

text:
why men’s self-care is a feminist issue//
.
all feminists should be deeply concerned with men’s self-care. here is one of dozens of stories that helps me explain why. —

just the other day i was walking from the parking lot to my office building in downtown los angeles. after avoiding a pile of human feces (we are five blocks from skid row) one of the two dogs i had with me decided to take a poop himself. as i reached for a poop bag i was mortified to realize they had fallen out in the car.

seeing as i was five feet from my office i decided that i’d drop the dogs off before returning to the car to retrieve the poop bags. then i’d clean up my contribution to the sidewalk. no big deal.

before i could take two steps i heard a voice scream, “no! where are you going? clean that up right now!” i turned around to see a white man on a cell phone violently waving his hand at me. he was the owner of the building next door to mine.

at first i was taken aback. i could feel the heat rise in my body as my fight/flight system kicked in. i was about to apologize, cower, and politely try to explain the situation. (honestly, i think i briefly considered picking up the poop in my bare hands). but instead, i snapped... .
💕 #kaseydreier #kd
.
📸 from @unsplash - erik owens

text:
“when the jesus most people have been taught to revere is little more than a well-dressed pile of principalities & powers in disguise, mark my words: the christianity that results has issued the prescription for its destruction in its own handwriting — & it will inevitably implode on its own hypocrisy over time.

we are all collectively bearing witness to the inevitable implosion of the americanized adaption of christianity right now. perhaps that seems an overreaction on my part but i assure you: it is not. over the series of the next few blog posts, i intend to systematically address the idolatry of four different baals currently masquerading as jesus in the church & as such are thus being worshipped accordingly.”
- moldable jesus part i: when jesus is dressed as shame
re: an exposé on modesty & purity culture

the first installment in a six part series. 
to read more click the link in my bio.

text:
we are grateful for @tribalmarkers and their gracious contribution to our convergence. getting our faces painted with their beautiful markers helped to activate the warrior within us all. 🔥 .

here @jason___mack dons @realization_nation in paint to match his vibrant spirit! fabian shares about his experience at the convergence: .

i witnessed this weekend the beginning of paradigm shift that has been long over due. the awakening of the #sacredmasculine 🙌 .

what an honor and blessing to be able to sit in ceremony with 70 men from around the world and bare witness to radical transformations that will ripple out far and wide. .

thank you to all the brothers that stepped up and anchored this down. my heart is full and renewed with new hope for the future generations to come. i look forward to being of service to you all again in future gatherings and having you all join me in peru. .

follow @sacredsons to stay tuned for up coming events. a big thank you to my brothers @jason___mack @adam___jackson @spiritualheart for spearheading this vision. we are rising. that’s what’s sacred. .

thank you fabian! we appreciate you and honor you as a sacred son! .

and thank you to all the men who are sharing about your experiences at the convergence. your words will inspire other men to rise up and we are happy to be able to include some of it here on our page. .

its now been three days out of the alchemical container of the convergence and many of us are being met with the privilege to face challenges that will test our resolve. can we remain centered in the face of life's tests? the only way forward is to keep doing the inner work and using the practices (breathwork, meditation, yoga, movement, etc.) we need to remain steadfast on this path. .

stay connected with your brothers and reach out! be the first to reach out, don't hold back and wait for someone to reach out to you. and if you need to recharge in sacred brotherhood join us at @communityhealing on 10/27 and at @onelovefestnow from 11/2 - 11/4 for our sacred masculine ceremony circles. use code 'sacred' for discounted passes passes to one love fest! hope to see you there! .

#sacredsons

its now been three days out of the alchemical container of the convergence and many of us are being met with the privilege to face challenges that will test our resolve. can we remain centered in the face of life's tests? the only way forward is to keep doing the inner work and using the practices (breathwork, meditation, yoga, movement, etc.) we need to remain steadfast on this path. .

stay connected with your brothers and reach out! be the first to reach out, do not hold back and wait for someone to reach out to you. and if you need to recharge in sacred brotherhood join us at  on 10/27 and at  from 11/2 - 11/4 for our sacred masculine ceremony circles. use code 'sacred' for discounted passes passes to one love fest! hope to see you there! .

text:
o segundo sexo (en galego)
autora: simone de beauvoir
editorial: @edicionsxeraisdegalicia

la conocida biblia del feminismo narrada por esta escritora con coraje y un pensamiento crítico que se podría transladar a la actualidad.analiza nuestro papel desde un punto de vista: filosófico,biológico,histórico,psicoanalítico...poniendo los puntos sobre las ies y sin dejar nada atrás en el tintero.
"la mujer es una mujer en la medida que ella se experimenta como tal"
"aparece la propiedad privada...y el hombre adquiere a la mujer como un objeto para hacer que se perpetúe su poder"
"no se puede obligar a la mujer a parir.pero si: imponer una ley, obligarla al matrimonio, prohibir los anticonceptivos,el divorcio y el aborto" "en la historia el mundo perteneció siempre al hombre" "no naces mujer,llegas a serlo"

text: shout out to the men who ask me about how they can make hip hop a safer, more inclusive space for women and then actually listen so they can do those things. inclusion is about more than adding women (please don’t say “female rappers”) to a line up. it’s also about the culture you create, the people you give decision-making power to, and the norms you reinforce. what does the promo material look like? what role do the women on stage play? what kind of environment is your host creating? there are so many opportunities to do better for the culture. text: with vulnerability the stronghold releases... it is uncomfortable and it is the hardest work one can do. sometimes it literally feels like ringing out your dna and filtering ancient fear receptors that consciously you want so badly to believe no longer serve you, but unconsciously you have been hardwired to feel the world is not a safe place. there is so much power in being vulnerable... who knew... this could be why so many peoples have been persecuted for so long. if anything will keep a people sick, down, and disconnected  it is the prolonged state of hyperarousal and constant feeling of needing to protect their basic human rights. society does not provide a canvas for vulnerability for those people who need it the most. often the most vulnerable people are in a constant survival state, judged by their lack. today i ask myself what can i do as a human and a woman to stand firmly in vulnerability ... knowing i will be judged? i can do it knowing it offers insight and courage to many and hold space for the judges because they too have their story 💜. #metoo #womenrise #indigenouswomenrise  #trauma #thebodyremembers #transformation #toxicpeople #domesticviolence #thebodykeepsthescore #complextrauma #thrive #vulnerability #strongwomen #ptsd #change #adversechildhoodexperiences #traumainformed #traumainformedclassrooms

text:
#couragedearheart 💜 i’ll be me and you be you, ‘cause the bravest hearts need heroes too. 💜... .
too many women are carrying burdens that don’t belong to them. the more i listen, the more i reach, the more i heal,  the more i teach, the more aware i become of deeply embedded suffering amongst the most outwardly confident women. this is not surprising, because we are raised to believe we are weak, fragile or incapable of truly protecting ourselves....and yet, we endure childbirth time and time again. so silencing pain is taught. silencing pain is encouraged. silencing shame is pressed deeper still. but, i have to say, what i have learned most by dedicating my time and professional services to women is this: they are scared of never being enough. enough of what? for whom? the list is endless but never painless. .
.
so, girls, ladies and women everywhere - take heed. you are absolutely and unequivocally enough. you are more than enough! you are magnificent! your body is uniquely designed to create, nurture and allure. your body is beautiful. your soul is impenetrable. your spirit is unconquerable. you have a purpose and you have a reason, and you are without a doubt an absolute badass! you were literally designed to survive the worst pain imaginable, and even if your destiny does not require this of you, you are designed to be a survivor regardless. it’s in you. your beauty is incomparable and your worth is immeasurable. .
.
further beautify yourself if you wish. replace or add elements if you desire. but, remember this....
.
.
you are magnificent exactly as you are and right now you are literally someone’s dream girl. #truth
.
.
someone’s #perfection . just. as. you. are.
.
.

text:
a few days ago, i was listening to dr. tedros adhanom ghebreyesus, the director-general of the world health organization (who), who spoke via video on the importance of our work on global health and education at the launch event of my 大阪大学（osaka university） mentor and professor dr. beverley yamamoto's unesco chair. that same night, friends and i went to watch a movie that revolves around mental health, and well-being (#astarisborn). next day, an article appeared in the the guardian, co-authored by dr. tedros and the star of that movie, co-founder of the born this way foundation, and an idol of mine, lady gaga. it reported that 800,000 people kill themselves every year (see below). we live around incredible human vulnerability and in the time of an emergency. 
with the relevance of #metoo and #noh8, the issues of mental health, sexual health, well-being, sexual orientation and gender identity expression (sogie) have gained traction. as a social scientist, analyst, a budding policymaker and diplomat, i think that my own pain, understanding of the intersectionality with other socio-economic indicators such as gender, race, religion, nationality, and so on; and their impact on outcomes in education and life-attainments in health and wealth (particularly, on one's pursuit of dignity and fulfillment, and in general, on international development), have enhanced my ability to to help 'heal' these issues. 
i am writing this post to indicate that i am taking inspiration from and being motivated by events and discourses all around me, and while dealing with my own pain, i am re-evaluating my future directions as it becomes clear to me where the next ambition of my heart lies in this career ride, as these experiences relate to how i have changed over the past one year. 
https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2018/oct/09/lady-gaga-mental-health-global-emergency-suicide

http://unescochair-ghe.org/

https://en.unesco.org/themes/education-health-and-well-being

text: what do you choose today?  i made a conscious choice today to be sober and clean. i prefer to feel my feelings today instead of mask them the way i did when i was under the influence.  life is so rich and the promises are alive in me. i experience love deeply and i can grieve in a healthy state of mind all of my past that i choose not to regret any longer. this has worked one day at a time for 27 years now.  i never believed that i would be sober and able to deal with my childhood trauma, yet it is now my biggest gift as i am able to help others as a result of step 12.  if you are new, you are the most important person in this program and i love you dearly!  know this, if i can make it, anyone can.  #theshamelesswarrior #recoveryispossible #metoo #timesup #metooneveryou #aa #onedayatatime #healtrauma #sobrietyrocks #soberwomen #traumahealing #recoveryispossible #sobrietyquotes #sobriety #rehab #rehabaddict #alcoholicsanonymous

text:
i have had the joy and pleasure to be trusted with such a large project for my internship. i could not have done it without @paige_benner ‘s editing and directing and @riley415 ‘s filming. .
.
.
in 2006, tarana burke started the #metoo movement as a way to create a dialogue and support system for survivors within communities of color. in 2017, the movement went viral. a massive online campaign lead to a groundswell of individuals from every gender, race, and sexuality sharing their stories of survival. though it’s empowering to see perpetrators being held accountable, it has been re-traumatizing for so many. “if you make something [like this] viral, you have to be prepared to help people deal,” burke said. “you have to give people something else besides the disclosure.” this year has been a whirlwind. however, the movement is not perfect, and we are not perfect. we want to acknowledge the challenges of all this attention, and get back to burke’s original intention: to start a conversation so that survivors can feel heard, validated, and supported.

to survivors: awakenings hears you, believes you, and supports you. it is hard enough to survive assault or abuse, let alone an entire year of re-traumatizing public scrutiny. to help you heal, we have events and workshops that span every modality of creative healing that we can think of. give it a try. but we also want to know: what do you need from us? how can we do better to support you?

to the greater community: we know the epidemic of sexual violence feels insurmountable. but there are ways you can make a difference: by supporting survivors. if you want to have a positive impact on a survivor’s life, come find us. volunteer, donate, or even share this video. starting a conversation about sexual assault with one person could make a difference. so start now.

text:
i was on swedish radio a couple days ago talking about #metoo. i figured out that i’ve been home for exactly six months now. in the course of these past six months, i’ve had quite a few bad encounters. first there was n, who turned out to be a possessive stalker. then there was v, who tried to rape me. (sadly, not the first time that has happened to me; nevertheless i thank myself everyday since, that i persevered and forced him off me) then there was h, who objectified and tried to emotionally manipulate me. been a quite intense and tiring six months, to say the least. 
the woman interviewing asked how the revolution has impacted me personally. i told her that i’m no longer afraid to speak my truth, because i know theres support now. warmth. stories to share. love. there’s been a lot of sexual violence in the time-frame of my life. it started when i was young. for a big part of it, i was ashamed. but like an epiphany i realized these things that happened to me, has never defined me or who i am. it has never been about me or my character. reliving that trauma is hard, but why should i feel ashamed for someone’s else’s actions?
how do we determine real courage? by staying silent? no more. my perception of it changed. strength isn’t about falling down and rising up, pushing through at whatever comes at you. it’s by telling, living and owning our truth. when we collectively make our voices heard, that’s when we find empowerment. real strength and character is pushing to be authentically yourself every god damn day of your life, and it’s bittersweet but oh so enlightening to the soul. here’s me speaking mine.🌹

text:
dreamingoutloud is nothing more than learning how to listen to the stories that want to be told, ⁣
ur soul’s  song⁣
⁣
these stories are part of ur shared ancestral memory or past life memories (i would wager that they are one in the same)  they are both comprised of the  life lessons each generation must learn to move to their next rite of passage⁣
⁣
these recurring themes are the key to discovering your 4 major emotional chords.  as a writer, u are the journalist/detective of the human condition ⁣
⁣
ur task is to learn how to ⁣
listen & investigate ⁣
those recurring notes ⁣
⁣
thedreamingoutloud technique ⁣
creates a safe, step-by-step ⁣
structure to download the stories ⁣
& analyze the recurring emotional chords. ⁣
⁣
soul-singing, transformative storytelling dwells in the places that scare us⁣ (thx @anipemachodron🧡) ⁣
the things u fear⁣
are the ancestral memories & past life lessons that u were put here to get right this time⁣
⁣
whatever the shit is that ⁣
broke u in the past, ⁣
thedreamingoutloud technique ⁣
takes that terror, ⁣
& weaves the pain into light⁣
& that’s the source of ur deepest
storytelling⁣
⁣
storytelling is what ⁣
actors do when they ⁣
inhabit another human being⁣
⁣
storytelling is what ⁣
writers do when they create psychologically complicated characters going on joseph campbell’s mythical hero’s journey⁣
⁣
storytelling ⁣
is what u do when u⁣
detach ⁣
from the matrix⁣
&  dare to ⁣
⁣
dreamoutloud⁣
to rewrite ur story⁣
to redefine ur life’s ⁣
purpose⁣
ur legacy ⁣
the places where ur⁣
soul⁣
is free⁣
to sing ⁣
her song⁣
⁣

actors⁣
writers ⁣
& dreamers⁣

text:
'ser casada com um ator poderoso me livrou do assédio', diz nicole kidman ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
em entrevista à revista new york magazine, a atriz nicole kidman, 51 anos revelou que o seu casamento com tom cruise, 56 anos, a livrou de sofrer assédio em hollywood. “eu me casei por amor, mas estar com um homem extremamente poderoso me livrou de assédio sexual”, afirmou em entrevista. kidman ficou casada por 11 anos com cruise, e o casal se separou em 2001. a atriz é casada atualmente com o músico keith urban, 50 anos.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
kidman conta que, depois de separada de cruise, ela passou por “momentos #metoo”, referindo-se ao movimento que uniu atrizes em um esforço para denunciar assédios sofridos ao longo de suas carreiras. sem dar muitos detalhes, na entrevista, ela afirma que esses casos de assédio ocorreram sim durante seus trabalhos como atriz. o assunto veio à tona já que a atriz foi escalada para um filme em que interpretará a jornalista gretchen carlson, que denunciou casos de assédio que ocorriam na fox news. o fundador e presidente do canal roger ailes foi processado por ela, em 2016.

text:
en 55 åring man påstår sig utvecklat känslor för en 15 årig  elev. vilket han mycket väl kan ha ansett sig ha men det är absolut inget försvar. skolan väljer att ge läraren en varning men han får behålla jobbet och alltså fortsätta ha kontakt med ytterligare unga elever. skolinspektionens svar på det hela är att eftersom läraren inte tagit ut lärarleg så kan de inte utreda saken... vi har alltså en situation där en hebefil får jobba kvar i en skola trots att han erkänt flertalet situationer där han "fått känslor" för sina elever och försökt inleda relationer med dem. en situation som uppstår för att mannen anses mer värd att skydda än eleverna. där jag gissar att en orsak till att skolan nöjer sig med en varning är att "inget skett". läraren har ju "bara" försökt få till träffar med eleven ensam och har ju "bara" varit för närgången. skolan verkar anse att de måste invänta att han faktiskt våldtar en elev innan de kan sparka honom för att han upprepade gånger försökt förföra elever på skolan... .
.
samtidigt som vi kan läsa om situationer som denna har #metoo nu nått indien med full kraft. svenska snubbars reaktioner på dessa saker? att metoo bara är fejk. att de hoppas att indiens rörelse inte "kapas" av ohederliga manshatande aktivister och att "feminismen gått för långt" i sverige. samt såklart den återkommande myten att det inte är män utan "scumbags" som beter sig som läraren eller random annan snubbe som korsar gränser för det acceptabla. denna 55 åring är en man och ett scumbag. det ena uteslutet inte det andra och det är fan på tiden att män ser sanningen i vitögat att det är andra män som våldtar, utnyttjar, försöker få till sex med småtjejer osv. män med olika typer av uppfostran, olika nivå av välartan, olika ekonomiska status, olika charm. de är fortfarande män, riktiga män som vem som helst. punkt slut.

text:
a serial killer’s daughter comes from three years of writing about my life alongside my father, dennis rader, the btk serial killer, and the aftermath left in the wake of his arrest.
.
even though it’s been 13 years since he was arrested, grief still comes and goes in waves, and trauma can still rear it’s ugly head in the form of ptsd. i live with daily struggles as a crime and trauma victim, and as the daughter of a vilified man.
.
it’s taken a long time to face all that my father did, and attempt to reconcile it with the man i knew, the one who raised me, that i loved.
.
i’ve gone through a long journey of healing since my father’s arrest, and writing has continued to help me recover.
.
being the daughter of a serial killer is rare, but i know many who carry unhealed wounds, and struggle to protect themselves and their families from the crippling effects of violence, anger, and loss.
.
i’m not alone in grappling with how to forgive the unforgivable; in attempting to rebuild life in the shadow of death.
.
it is my hope that my story will bring others hope. that it will help them along their journeys of grief, loss, forgiveness, and recovery.
.
somewhere along the way, i became a survivor, who continues to cling to resilience and resistance in faith, love, and my sure, stubbornness to never give up.
.
a serial killer’s daughter: my story of faith, love, and overcoming is now available to order from all major bookstores. link in my profile.

it’s taken a long time to face all that my father did, and attempt to reconcile it with the man i knew, the one who raised me, that i loved.
.
i’ve gone through a long journey of healing since my father’s arrest, and writing has continued to help me recover.
.
being the daughter of a serial killer is rare, but i know many who carry unhealed wounds, and struggle to protect themselves and their families from the crippling effects of violence, anger, and loss.
.
i’m not alone in grappling with how to forgive the unforgivable; in attempting to rebuild life in the shadow of death.
.
it is my hope that my story will bring others hope. that it will help them along their journeys of grief, loss, forgiveness, and recovery.
.
somewhere along the way, i became a survivor, who continues to cling to resilience and resistance in faith, love, and my sure, stubbornness to never give up.
.
a serial killer’s daughter: my story of faith, love, and overcoming is now available to order from all major bookstores. link in my profile.

text:
working through mental health issues feels like a never-ending battle. every time you take a step forward, something can happen and take you back another ten.
.
with the metoo conversation constantly surrounding us now i have been feeling very drained and vulnerable. i have nightmares in which i see the faces of previous molesters, where i'm trying to run away from them but they have a gun and are trying to shoot me before i can open my mouth to speak. naturally i have been waking up anxious, but i have also spent a lot of my waking life thinking about silence and how exhausting it can be. is not speaking up, naming names, writing opinion pieces cowardice; or is it simply that my journey to healing is different from others? the pressure to join in solidarity, to speak in absolutes and banish all nuance is tremendous. no wonder i am tired.
.
i have been lagging behind on my self-care, getting little exercise, forgetting to be mindful, and skipping my multivitamins. i have also been filling my days with work and social obligations. solitude seems unbearable, gratitude out of reach.
.
i don't know why i am sharing this picture today. maybe it is because it takes me back to greener times, to a place of quietude. or maybe i want to remind my inner voice to go easy on myself: not everyone moves at the same pace. sometimes even staying still can be a tiny victory when the earth is shaking beneath you.
.
#anxiety #nightmares #greenery #slowandsteady #breathe #mindfulness #healing #metoo

.
with the metoo conversation constantly surrounding us now i have been feeling very drained and vulnerable. i have nightmares in which i see the faces of previous molesters, where i am trying to run away from them but they have a gun and are trying to shoot me before i can open my mouth to speak. naturally i have been waking up anxious, but i have also spent a lot of my waking life thinking about silence and how exhausting it can be. is not speaking up, naming names, writing opinion pieces cowardice; or is it simply that my journey to healing is different from others? the pressure to join in solidarity, to speak in absolutes and banish all nuance is tremendous. no wonder i am tired.
.
i have been lagging behind on my self-care, getting little exercise, forgetting to be mindful, and skipping my multivitamins. i have also been filling my days with work and social obligations. solitude seems unbearable, gratitude out of reach.
.
i do not know why i am sharing this picture today. maybe it is because it takes me back to greener times, to a place of quietude. or maybe i want to remind my inner voice to go easy on myself: not everyone moves at the same pace. sometimes even staying still can be a tiny victory when the earth is shaking beneath you.
.
#anxiety #nightmares #greenery #slowandsteady #breathe #mindfulness #healing #metoo

text:
let's talk about patriarchy... what is it?

it is the system of society or government in which the wounded masculine holds the power and all others are largely excluded from it. its underlying motus operandi is to separate and control. not only do we see this in gender, it is also accomplished through race, religious discrimination, political polarities, nationalities and any other concept that promotes an 'us vs. them' attitude. it is also means to separate ourselves from self.  advertising, entertainment and commercial programming tells us we are not good enough, thin enough, wealthy enough, educated enough, etc thereby creating a fundamental deficit in our inherent worth as individuals. ✨when a culture like this is able to effectively keep us separate from each other and from our true selves, it has ultimate control. it tells us what to think, what to value, who to hate, who to love, what to be scared of, what to trust, how to spend our money, whats important, what is taboo, what is normal, etc, etc, etc.

separation = total control.

this is why it is more important than ever for us as a humanity to take back control and start to make decisions for ourselves based in love, compassion, trust and truth. that is why we use the hashtag #fuckthepartriarchy. 
its for all men and women of all backgrounds to put a stop to the incessant separation within ourselves and between ourselves. let us reclaim our powers!!! w.i.t.c.h. woman-invoking-truth-consciousness-here

text:
are you afraid of #metoo? 
with a growing list of celebrities, politicians, and pastors (yes, #churchtoo) being accused of sexual misconduct, some have suggested that this is actually a very scary time to be a man. let’s look at the numbers:

the percentage of unreported rapes is between 54-90%. out of 100 reported rapes, on average:
~30 face trial
~15 are jailed
~7 are false accusations

as a whole, we are a society of men more willing to allow women to be raped and to suffer without justice than to run the fractionally small risk that we might possibly be falsely accused. if that is what it means to be a man, it truly is a scary time. 
are we drawing a limiting line rather than extending a compassionate hand?

are there times when we are saying men are free from responsibility and women deserve to be raped?

as these questions intersect with our faith, how can we respond in a way that reflects our desire to embody christ’s love? 🙋‍♂️link in bio 🙅‍♀️

text:
.
"i decided today i wanted to take the pawer back."
"we have the power to fight back when we're silenced."
굉장히 인상깊은 스피치라 같이 보고 싶어 공유합니다.
제25회 elle woman in hollywood 행사에서
레이디가가의 스피치에요.
저는 패션, 멋, 의복에 대한 일이
평생 할 업 중 하나인 페미니스트(가 되고 싶은 사람)로서
코르셋과 (전문적)패션 사이에서의 고민이 항상 많은데요..
엘르 행사에서 할리우드 문화예술계 내 성폭력과
여성 엔터테이너로서 진심어린 이야기를 전하는
가가의 스피치를 보고 강한 연대감을 느꼈습니다.
@elleusa 이 계정의 igtv를 보시면
레이디가가의 스피치 전부를 세 영상에 걸쳐 보실 수 있어요.
.
"i asked myself:
what does it really mean to be a woman in hollywood?
we are not just objects to entertain the world.
we are not simply images
to bring smiles or grimaces to people’s faces.
we are not members of a giant beauty pageant
meant to be pit against one another
for the pleasure of the public.
we women in hollywood, we are voices.
we have deep thoughts and ideas and beliefs and values
about the world and we have the power
to speak and be heard and fight back
when we are silenced."
.

text:
speaker announcement! we are thrilled to have @searac california director joining us on november 3rd!!
.
nkauj iab yang is the california director with the southeast asia resource action center (searac). she works closely with southeast asian american led and serving organizations throughout california to build a statewide southeast asian american equity agenda, identify the appropriate strategies, and advocate for local and state policy change. nkauj iab spent the last 11 years committed to youth organizing and youth development work both in sacramento and oakland.
.
before coming to searac, nkauj iab served as the program manager with banteay srei, overseeing programs and direct services for southeast asian american young women impacted by sexual exploitation. through banteay srei, nkauj iab led a small collaborative to pass the resolution to expand and report disaggregated asian american and pacific islander data at oakland unified school district. .
learn more about @searac ! 
#aapirising #aapiwomenlead #api #womenofcolor #searac #imready
#sanfrancisco #southeastasian #intersectionalfeminism #intersectional #metoomvmt #metoo #whyididntreport #survivors  #oakland #sanfrancisco #berkeley

text: this post is going to be really personal. i am a survivor of rape. it makes me really sad to see all these men more worried about being falsely accused than the actual problem itself. in reality there are 2-8% false accusations. i never came forward. melenia trump stated that she thinks women need evidence that they are in fact victims. if i tried to point out my rapists to you there would be no evidence. that doesn’t make it any less real to me or any else real to others. it is important for all of us to stick together and support our women and femmes. i believe you and i hear your stories.  you are not invalid. this is also why it is so important for all of us to vote.  vote against people like trump.  #metoo

text:
well.
there’s been a hype everywhere about so many things i have been observing lately and i felt a bit responsible to come up with what i have doing myself. self-introspection and thinking about all of it.
let’s start with, #metoo 
sharing is caring. we all know. but no, some of us are making sarcastic jokes about those who have been opening up after so many years to everyone.
being molested at any age is a disturbing experience. like a burnt scar on the skin. it might heal but the experience is forever imprinted on the soul. opening up and stating it out is another disturbing thing to follow. why? because any gender who has been molested in any way looks down upon themselves. ever thought of confessing a lie that you told someone? just likewise, only million times worse. coming to terms with wrong doings to self of any kind is a troubling experience. please learn empathising and help healing. 
second thing is #depression.
depression is not a taboo just another illness none of us deserve to have. when someone does tell you of it? please be kind and attentive. being extra warm or being extra motivating is not what that person needs, being kind is enough. no gyan or no passive statements either. please understand the other person is human too just drowning in pain and sorrows more often than you. 
third is #mentaldisorder 
ever thought of how selfish it is that we only become kind towards those who are suffering from a mental disorder? how’s that even fair?
if a person has autism or dyslexia or even als, only then you’ll have an enlightened mind? that life is too short? isn’t it short anyway? 
fourth is #ailments 
so, your friend or close relative or some acquaintance died of cancer or something similar, and suddenly you have regrets. and god forbid, if that was a loved one, you feel drained of emotions. 
excuse me? what are you? isn’t life anyway unpredictable? aren’t you supposed to be human and value all the time you have?
give yourself a reality check. 
#realitycheck #notapologizing #mentalhealthawareness #evolve #stoppretending #stopdrama #metoomovement #lifeanddeath #disease #depressionawareness #helpeachother

text:
jag har under två dagar varit i österrike i egenskap av journalist och representant hos europeiska jämställdhetsinstitutet (european institute for gender equality, eige) för att ta del av deras arbete. fokus har bland annat varit på institutets rapport om jämställdhet (mellan binära kön) på nätet i europa.
🇪🇺
jag kommer dela med mig av mer senare, men här är några saker jag har fått veta om unga män och pojkar i europa:
▪️
unga män tenderar att ignorera eller förminska trakasserier de utsätts för på nätet på grund av förväntningen att de ”ska vara tuffa”.
▪️
”jag tror att killar har svårare att prata om saker. även om vi trakasseras av andra pratar vi inte om det”, säger en 16-årig pojke som intervjuats i rapporten.
▪️
unga män möts regelbundet av bilder på nätet där kvinnor objektifieras och aggressivitet tolereras. de möts också oftare än andra av innehåll som främjar rasism eller religiös extremism.
▪️
det är vanligt att pojkar hotar med att göra slut eller bruka fysiskt våld när deras partner eller andra vägra skicka nakenbilder till dem.
▪️
”toxic masculinity” pekas ut som en av bakomliggande faktorer till att pojkar pressar andra på nakenbilder, ägnar sig åt slut-shaming och sprider homofobi på nätet.
▪️
hur motverkar vi giftig maskulinitet?
”förebilder kan göra stor skillnad. men tyvärr ser vi många exempel där mäktiga män kommer undan; under #metoo har vi sett många anklagelser men få konsekvenser. jag är rädd att många unga män får en bild av att man kan komma undan med hemska, våldsamma beteenden”, svarar blandine mollard, forskningsledare på eige.
▪️
#stoppamachokulturen #tasnacket #frånensnubbetillenannan #eige #europeaninstituteforgenderequality #toxicmasculinity

text:
last night, i finally watched city of joy on netflix. it has been on my watchlist, but after @drdenismukwege (founder, gynecologist and activist) was awarded the #2018nobelpeaceprize i knew it was time. .
"how does one find joy amid unspeakable tragedy? madeleine gavin’s documentary is about a community built around women who have survived horrific violence in the democratic republic of congo (drc) and gives us a glimpse at both an incredible injustice still occurring today and how congolese women are combating it with their own grassroots movement.” .
this morning’s sketch was inspired by this documentary. the image of the vagina stands at the center of two opposing forces representing both the darkness (violence, cruelty, pain, isolation...) and the light (strength, release, rebirth, freedom....) in the past, i would have watched this film and let it sit with me for days, if not weeks. instead, i use my art as a way to release the emotions that move through me on to paper. as an empath and someone who cares so deeply, my morning sketching has become a tool for my mental well being.

i dedicate this sketch to any victim who has experienced sexual trauma or assault. you are not alone. you can, and will, find joy in the aftermath. let the women of the congo be a reminder of this truth. watch the film and prepare to be inspired!
